184         public void assignFunctionsToControlFlowGraphNodes() {
185             for (TacFunction function : this.userFunctions.values()) {
186                 assignFunctionToControlFlowGraphNode(function);
187             }
188     
189             // for each method: repeat the same
190             for (TacFunction function : this.getMethods()) {
191                 assignFunctionToControlFlowGraphNode(function);
192             }
193         }
194     
195         private void assignFunctionToControlFlowGraphNode(TacFunction function) {
196             if (function == null) {
197                 throw new RuntimeException("SNH");
198             }
199     
200             // handle normal function controlFlowGraph
201             ControlFlowGraph controlFlowGraph = function.getControlFlowGraph();
202             this.assignFunctionsHelper(controlFlowGraph, function);
203     
204             // handle function default controlFlowGraphs
205             for (TacFormalParameter parameter : function.getParams()) {
206                 if (parameter.hasDefault()) {
207                     ControlFlowGraph defaultControlFlowGraph = parameter.getDefaultControlFlowGraph();
208                     this.assignFunctionsHelper(defaultControlFlowGraph, function);
209                 }
210             }
211         }
212     
213         private void assignFunctionsHelper(ControlFlowGraph controlFlowGraph, TacFunction function) {
214             for (AbstractCfgNode node : controlFlowGraph.dfPreOrder()) {
215                 node.setEnclosingFunction(function);
216     
217                 // enter basic block
218                 if (node instanceof BasicBlock) {
219                     BasicBlock bb = (BasicBlock) node;
220                     for (AbstractCfgNode contained : bb.getContainedNodes()) {
221                         contained.setEnclosingFunction(function);
222                     }
223                 }
224             }
225         }

227         // note: for function default cfgs (for default parameters), no basic blocks
228         // are created (because it would be useless); don't change this behavior, or
229         // you will get into trouble in other places
230         public void createBasicBlocks() {
231             // which cfg nodes did we already visit?
232             Set<AbstractCfgNode> visited = new HashSet<>();
233     
234             // for each function cfg...
235             for (TacFunction function : this.userFunctions.values()) {
236                 ControlFlowGraph controlFlowGraph = function.getControlFlowGraph();
237                 AbstractCfgNode head = controlFlowGraph.getHead();
238                 visited.add(head);
239                 this.createBasicBlocksHelper(head.getSuccessor(0), visited);
240             }
241             // for each method cfg...
242             for (TacFunction function : this.getMethods()) {
243                 ControlFlowGraph controlFlowGraph = function.getControlFlowGraph();
244                 AbstractCfgNode head = controlFlowGraph.getHead();
245                 visited.add(head);
246                 this.createBasicBlocksHelper(head.getSuccessor(0), visited);
247             }
248         }
249     
250         // LATER: non-recursive implementation (stack is getting deep);
251         // receives a node that might be the beginning of a basic block
252         private void createBasicBlocksHelper(AbstractCfgNode cfgNode, Set<AbstractCfgNode> visited) {
253             if (visited.contains(cfgNode)) {
254                 // we've already been here: don't go any further
255                 return;
256             }
257             visited.add(cfgNode);
258     
259             if (this.allowedInBasicBlock(cfgNode)) {
260                 // start basic block!
261     
262                 // number of nodes contained in this new basic block
263                 int contained = 1;
264     
265                 // edges that shall enter the basic block
266                 List<CfgEdge> inEdges = cfgNode.getInEdges();
267     
268                 // the first node in the basic block
269                 AbstractCfgNode startNode = cfgNode;
270     
271                 // the basic block
272                 BasicBlock basicBlock = new BasicBlock(startNode);
273     
274                 // all nodes that are allowed to be in a basic block
275                 // have 1 or no successors
276                 AbstractCfgNode succ = startNode.getSuccessor(0);
277                 AbstractCfgNode beforeSucc = startNode;
278                 while (succ != null && this.allowedInBasicBlock(succ) && !visited.contains(succ)) {
279                     if (succ.getPredecessors().size() > 1) {
280                         // if the successor node has more than 1 predecessors,
281                         // we must not continue with our basic block here
282                         break;
283                     }
284                     visited.add(succ);
285                     basicBlock.addNode(succ);
286                     contained++;
287                     beforeSucc = succ;
288                     succ = succ.getSuccessor(0);
289                 }
290     
291                 // if this is not a one-element basic block...
292                 // (i.e., does not create single-node basic blocks)
293                 if (contained > 1) {
294                     startNode.clearInEdges();
295                     basicBlock.informEnclosedNodes();
296     
297                     // embed basic block:
298                     // connect with predecessors
299                     for (CfgEdge inEdge : inEdges) {
300                         inEdge.setDestination(basicBlock);
301                         basicBlock.addInEdge(inEdge);
302                     }
303                     // connect with successor
304                     beforeSucc.clearOutEdges();
305                     if (succ != null) {
306                         succ.removeInEdge(beforeSucc);
307                         CfgEdge blockToSucc = new CfgEdge(basicBlock, succ, CfgEdge.NORMAL_EDGE);
308                         basicBlock.setOutEdge(0, blockToSucc);
309                         succ.addInEdge(blockToSucc);
310                     }
311                 }
312     
313                 if (succ != null) {
314                     // continue algorithm at successor node
315                     this.createBasicBlocksHelper(succ, visited);
316                 }
317             } else {
318                 // try successors
319                 List<AbstractCfgNode> successors = cfgNode.getSuccessors();
320                 for (AbstractCfgNode successor : successors) {
321                     this.createBasicBlocksHelper(successor, visited);
322                 }
323             }
324         }
325     
326         private boolean allowedInBasicBlock(AbstractCfgNode cfgNode) {
327             // EFF: use a field inside CfgNode* instead;
328             // note: alias information must not change inside basic blocks
329     
330             if (cfgNode instanceof CallBuiltinFunction) {
331                 // allow calls to builtin functions to appear inside basic blocks,
332                 // but only if these builtin functions are not used as sinks
333                 // in later analyses
334                 CallBuiltinFunction cfgNodeBuiltin = (CallBuiltinFunction) cfgNode;
335                 return !MyOptions.isSink(cfgNodeBuiltin.getFunctionName());
336             } else if (cfgNode instanceof AssignSimple ||
337                 cfgNode instanceof AssignUnary ||
338                 cfgNode instanceof AssignBinary ||
339                 cfgNode instanceof Define ||
340                 cfgNode instanceof EmptyTest ||
341                 cfgNode instanceof Isset ||
342                 cfgNode instanceof Static
343             ) {
344                 return true;
345             }
346     
347             return false;
348         }

350         // includes the given converter at the specified include node;
351         // includingFunction: the one that contains the include node
352         public void include(TacConverter includedTac, Include includeNode, TacFunction includingFunction) {
353             // INLINE MAIN CFG *************************************
354     
355             // functions inside the included file
356             Map<String, TacFunction> includedUserFunctions = includedTac.getUserFunctions();
357     
358             // retrieve main cfg that is to be included
359             TacFunction includedMainFunc = includedUserFunctions.get(InternalStrings.mainFunctionName);
360     
361             this.inlineMainCfg(includedMainFunc, includeNode);
362     
363             // add function and method calls inside the included main function (for backpatching)
364             this.addFunctionCalls(this.mainFunction, includedTac.getFunctionCalls(includedMainFunc));
365             this.addMethodCalls(this.mainFunction, includedTac.getMethodCalls(includedMainFunc));
366     
367             // EXPAND SYMBOL TABLE **************************************
368     
369             // the symbol table of the function that the include node belongs to
370             // has to be expanded with the contents of the symbol table of the
371             // main function of the included file
372     
373             SymbolTable includedMainSymTab = includedMainFunc.getSymbolTable();
374             SymbolTable includingSymTab = includingFunction.getSymbolTable();
375     
376             includingSymTab.addAll(includedMainSymTab);
377             includedMainSymTab = null;  // don't forget that you must trash it now
378     
379             // ADD FUNCTIONS ********************************************
380     
381             for (TacFunction includedFunc : includedUserFunctions.values()) {
382                 if (includedFunc.isMain()) {
383                     // we have already dealt with the main function above
384                     continue;
385                 }
386     
387                 String includedFuncName = includedFunc.getName();
388     
389                 // does this function already exist here?
390                 TacFunction existingFunction = this.userFunctions.get(includedFuncName);
391                 if (existingFunction != null) {
392                     // only issue a warning if they are not from the same file
393                     if (!existingFunction.getFileName().equals(includedFunc.getFileName())) {
394                         System.out.println("\nWarning: Duplicate function definition due to include: " + includedFuncName);
395                         System.out.println("- tried: " + includedFunc.getLoc());
396                         System.out.println("- using: " + existingFunction.getLoc());
397                     }
398                     continue;
399                 }
400     
401                 this.userFunctions.put(includedFuncName, includedFunc);
402     
403                 // add method and function calls inside this function (for backpatching)
404                 this.addFunctionCalls(includedFunc, includedTac.getFunctionCalls(includedFunc));
405                 this.addMethodCalls(includedFunc, includedTac.getMethodCalls(includedFunc));
406             }
407     
408             // add the call nodes contained in the included main function to the
409             // list of call nodes contained in the including function
410             //includingFunction.addContainedCalls(includedMainFunc.getContainedCalls());
411     
412             // TacFunction.calledFrom field doesn't need to be updated here:
413             // is performed by the call to Call.setFunction in TacConverter.backpatch
414     
415             // ADD CLASSES / METHODS ************************************
416     
417             // methods inside the included file
418             Map<String, Map<String, TacFunction>> includedUserMethods = includedTac.getUserMethods();
419     
420             for (Map.Entry<String, Map<String, TacFunction>> entry1 : includedUserMethods.entrySet()) {
421                 String includedMethodName = entry1.getKey();
422     
423                 for (Map.Entry<String, TacFunction> entry2 : entry1.getValue().entrySet()) {
424                     String className = entry2.getKey();
425                     TacFunction includedMethod = entry2.getValue();
426     
427                     // try to add this method
428                     TacFunction existingMethod = this.addMethod(includedMethodName, className, includedMethod);
429     
430                     // if there already exists such a method...
431                     if (existingMethod != null) {
432     
433                         // only issue a warning if they are not from the same file;
434                         // reason: if they are from the same file, it probably means that
435                         // this file was included more than once;
436                         // another possibility is that there is a real duplicate method definition
437                         // in the one file, but then, a warning for this was already issued
438                         // during the conversion of this file
439                         if (!existingMethod.getFileName().equals(includedMethod.getFileName())) {
440                             System.out.println("\nWarning: Duplicate method definition due to include: " + includedMethodName);
441                             System.out.println("- found: " + includedMethod.getLoc());
442                             System.out.println("- using: " + existingMethod.getLoc());
443                         }
444     
445                         continue;
446                     }
447     
448                     // add method and function calls inside this method (for backpatching)
449                     this.addFunctionCalls(includedMethod, includedTac.getFunctionCalls(includedMethod));
450                     this.addMethodCalls(includedMethod, includedTac.getMethodCalls(includedMethod));
451                 }
452             }
453     
454             // add class info
455             for (Map.Entry<String, TacClass> entry : includedTac.userClasses.entrySet()) {
456                 String includedClassName = entry.getKey();
457                 TacClass includedClass = entry.getValue();
458                 TacClass existingClass = this.userClasses.get(includedClassName);
459                 if (existingClass == null) {
460                     this.userClasses.put(includedClassName, includedClass);
461                 } else {
462                     // see comment about methods above (analogous)
463                     if (!existingClass.getFileName().equals(includedClass.getFileName())) {
464                         System.out.println("\nWarning: Duplicate class definition due to include: " + includedClassName);
465                         System.out.println("- found: " + includedClass.getLoc());
466                         System.out.println("- using: " + existingClass.getLoc());
467                     }
468                 }
469             }
470     
471             // no need to add anything for the special symbol table
472     
473             // CONSTANTS TABLE **********************
474     
475             this.constantsTable.addAll(includedTac.getConstantsTable());
476     
477             // ADJUST INCLUDED INCLUDE NODES *********************
478     
479             List<Include> includedIncludeNodes = includedTac.getIncludeNodes();
480             for (Include includedIncludeNode : includedIncludeNodes) {
481                 if (includedIncludeNode.getIncludeFunction().isMain()) {
482                     includedIncludeNode.setIncludeFunction(includingFunction);
483                 }
484             }
485     
486             // HOTSPOTS
487     
488             if (this.specialNodeMarkersShouldBeConsidered) {
489                 this.hotspots.putAll(includedTac.hotspots);
490             }
491         }

493         // helper function for "include": inlines the main CFG
494         private void inlineMainCfg(TacFunction includedMainFunc, Include includeNode) {
495             ControlFlowGraph includedMainControlFlowGraph = includedMainFunc.getControlFlowGraph();
496     
497             // entry and exit nodes of the included file's main cfg
498             CfgEntry includedEntry = (CfgEntry) includedMainControlFlowGraph.getHead();
499             CfgExit includedExit = (CfgExit) includedMainControlFlowGraph.getTail();
500     
501             // node after the entry
502             AbstractCfgNode afterEntry = includedEntry.getSuccessor(0);
503     
504             // if this main cfg consists only of entry and exit node:
505             // simply remove the include node
506             if (afterEntry instanceof CfgExit) {
507                 this.removeCfgNode(includeNode);
508             } else {
509                 IncludeStart includeStart = new IncludeStart(includeNode.getFile(), includeNode.getParseNode());
510                 IncludeEnd includeEnd = new IncludeEnd(includeStart);
511     
512                 // edges entering the exit
513                 List<CfgEdge> beforeExitList = includedExit.getInEdges();
514     
515                 // edges entering and leaving the "include" node in the including file
516                 List<CfgEdge> includeInEdges = includeNode.getInEdges();
517                 CfgEdge[] includeOutEdges = includeNode.getOutEdges();
518     
519                 // node after the "include" node
520                 AbstractCfgNode afterInclude;
521                 try {
522                     afterInclude = includeOutEdges[0].getDestination();
523                 } catch (NullPointerException e) {
524                     System.out.println(includeNode.getLoc());
525                     throw e;
526                 }
527     
528                 // remove edges (from the nodes' point of view)
529                 afterInclude.removeInEdge(includeNode);
530                 afterEntry.removeInEdge(includedEntry);
531     
532                 // redirect edges that enter the include node to includeStart
533                 for (CfgEdge inEdge : includeInEdges) {
534                     inEdge.setDestination(includeStart);
535                     includeStart.addInEdge(inEdge);
536                 }
537     
538                 // connect includeStart with the node following the
539                 // included cfg's entry node
540                 connect(includeStart, afterEntry);
541     
542                 // redirect edges that enter the included cfg's exit node to includeEnd
543                 for (CfgEdge inEdge : beforeExitList) {
544                     inEdge.setDestination(includeEnd);
545                     includeEnd.addInEdge(inEdge);
546                 }
547     
548                 // connect includeEnd with the node following the include node
549                 connect(includeEnd, afterInclude);
550             }
551         }

553         // resets the global tempId to the given logId;
554         // use this method because it maintains maximumTemporaryId
555         private void resetId(int logId) {
556             if (this.tempId > this.maximumTemporaryId) {
557                 this.maximumTemporaryId = tempId;
558             }
559             this.tempId = logId;
560         }

573         private Variable newTemp(TacFunction function) {
574     
575             String varName = "_t" + this.tempId++ + "_" + this.id;
576             SymbolTable symbolTable = function.getSymbolTable();
577     
578             // try to recycle existing temporary
579             Variable variable = symbolTable.getVariable(varName);
580     
581             // if it doesn't exist: create new one
582             if (variable == null) {
583                 variable = new Variable(varName, symbolTable, true);
584                 symbolTable.add(variable);
585             }
586     
587             return variable;
588         }
589     
590         private Variable newTemp() {
591             return this.newTemp(this.functionStack.getLast());
592         }

647         // prints statistical information
648         public void stats() {
649             // global variables
650             int globalVarsReal = 0;
651             int globalVarsTemp = 0;
652             for (Variable globalVar : this.mainFunctionSymbolTable.getVariablesColl()) {
653                 if (globalVar.isTemp()) {
654                     globalVarsTemp++;
655                 } else {
656                     globalVarsReal++;
657                 }
658             }
659     
660             if (MyOptions.optionV) {
661                 System.out.println("global variables (real): " + globalVarsReal);
662                 System.out.println("global variables (temp): " + globalVarsTemp);
663             }
664     
665             int tempsTotal = globalVarsTemp;
666             int gShadowsTotal = 0;
667             int fShadowsTotal = 0;
668             int normalLocalsTotal = 0;
669     
670             for (TacFunction userFunction : this.userFunctions.values()) {
671                 if (userFunction.isMain()) {
672                     // the stats for the main function were already extracted above
673                     continue;
674                 }
675                 Collection<Variable> vars = userFunction.getSymbolTable().getVariablesColl();
676     
677                 int temps = 0;
678                 for (Variable var : vars) {
679                     if (var.isTemp()) {
680                         temps++;
681                     }
682                 }
683                 int gShadows = userFunction.getSymbolTable().getGlobals2GShadows().size();
684                 int fShadows = userFunction.getSymbolTable().getFormals2FShadows().size();
685                 int normalLocals = vars.size() - temps - gShadows - fShadows;
686     
687                 tempsTotal += temps;
688                 gShadowsTotal += gShadows;
689                 fShadowsTotal += fShadows;
690                 normalLocalsTotal += normalLocals;
691             }
692     
693             if (MyOptions.optionV) {
694                 System.out.println();
695                 System.out.println("Functions:     " + (this.userFunctions.size() - 1));
696                 System.out.println("Normal Locals: " + normalLocalsTotal);
697                 System.out.println("Temps:         " + tempsTotal);
698                 System.out.println("G-Shadows:     " + gShadowsTotal);
699                 System.out.println("F-Shadows:     " + fShadowsTotal);
700                 System.out.println();
701                 System.out.println("Constants Table size: " + this.constantsTable.size());
702                 System.out.println("SuperSymTab size:     " + this.superglobalsSymbolTable.size());
703                 System.out.println("Special SymTab size:  " + this.specialVariablesSymbolTable.size());
704                 System.out.println();
705                 System.out.println("Classes: " + this.userClasses.size());
706             }
707         }

772         // removes empty nodes from a controlFlowGraph;
773         // the controlFlowGraph must have at least one non-empty node;
774         private void removeEmptyNodesFromCfg(ControlFlowGraph controlFlowGraph) {
775             AbstractCfgNode startHere;
776     
777             // remove leading empty nodes
778             // (requires "head" adjustment)
779             for (startHere = controlFlowGraph.getHead(); startHere instanceof Empty; ) {
780                 startHere = removeCfgNode(startHere);
781             }
782             controlFlowGraph.setHead(startHere);
783     
784             // remove remaining empty nodes
785             for (AbstractCfgNode current : controlFlowGraph.dfPreOrder()) {
786                 if (current instanceof Empty) {
787                     this.removeCfgNode(current);
788                 }
789             }
790         }
791     
792         // removes empty cfg node and returns successor
793         private AbstractCfgNode removeCfgNode(AbstractCfgNode cfgNode) {
794             // empty nodes have at most one successor:
795             CfgEdge outEdge = cfgNode.getOutEdge(0);
796             List<CfgEdge> inEdges = cfgNode.getInEdges();
797             if (outEdge != null) {
798                 AbstractCfgNode succ = outEdge.getDestination();
799     
800                 // remove this edge (from the viewpoint of the successor)
801                 succ.removeInEdge(cfgNode);
802     
803                 // redirect all incoming nodes to this successor node:
804                 for (CfgEdge inEdge : inEdges) {
805                     inEdge.setDestination(succ);
806                     succ.addInEdge(inEdge);
807                 }
808                 return succ;
809             } else {
810                 // this node is a dead end: don't do anything;
811                 // why you should not remove it: might be the first
812                 // statement after a branch, would screw up the CFG
813                 return null;
814             }
815         }

817         // replaces literal entries of the $GLOBALS array in the given CFG with
818         // the corresponding global variables (i.e., with local variables of the
819         // main function)
820         private void transformGlobals(ControlFlowGraph controlFlowGraph) {
821             Variable globalsArray = this.superglobalsSymbolTable.getVariable("$GLOBALS");
822     
823             // traverse CFG...
824             for (AbstractCfgNode cfgNode : controlFlowGraph.dfPreOrder()) {
825                 // inspect this node's variables...
826                 int varCount = -1;
827                 for (Variable var : cfgNode.getVariables()) {
828                     varCount++;
829     
830                     // nothing to do for placeholders
831                     if (var == null) {
832                         continue;
833                     }
834     
835                     // nothing to do for non-array-elements
836                     if (!var.isArrayElement()) {
837                         continue;
838                     }
839     
840                     // nothing to do for array elements whose top enclosing array
841                     // is not the $GLOBALS array
842                     if (!(var.getTopEnclosingArray().equals(globalsArray))) {
843                         continue;
844                     }
845     
846                     // at this point, we can't do anything for elements with
847                     // non-literal indices
848                     if (var.hasNonLiteralIndices()) {
849                         continue;
850                     }
851     
852                     // construct name of the corresponding main local
853                     StringBuilder varNameBuffer = new StringBuilder();
854                     varNameBuffer.append("$");
855                     Iterator<AbstractTacPlace> indicesIter = var.getIndices().iterator();
856                     AbstractTacPlace firstIndex = indicesIter.next();
857                     varNameBuffer.append(firstIndex.getLiteral().toString());
858                     while (indicesIter.hasNext()) {
859                         AbstractTacPlace index = indicesIter.next();
860                         varNameBuffer.append("[");
861                         varNameBuffer.append(index.getLiteral().toString());
862                         varNameBuffer.append("]");
863                     }
864                     String varName = varNameBuffer.toString();
865     
866                     // retrieve/create the corresponding variable and use it as replacement
867                     Variable transformedVar = this.makePlace(varName, this.mainFunctionSymbolTable);
868                     cfgNode.replaceVariable(varCount, transformedVar);
869                 }
870             }
871         }
872     
873         // scans the program for "global" statements; replaces local function variables
874         // with global variables accordingly; e.g., if it finds the statement
875         // "global $x" in function foo, it replaces all occurrences of the local variable
876         // $x in foo with the global variable $x; note that this is not correct in
877         // all cases (not flow-sensitive), but it provides good results in practice;
878         // this should only be used if a full-fledged alias analysis is not desired
879         void replaceGlobals() {
880             // for each user-defined function...
881             for (TacFunction userFunction : this.userFunctions.values()) {
882     
883                 if (userFunction.isMain()) {
884                     // nothing to do for the main function
885                     continue;
886                 }
887     
888                 // info retrieval *******
889     
890                 // retrieve a set of variables that have been declared as "global";
891                 // mapping "variable name" -> "global variable"
892                 Map<String, Variable> declaredAsGlobal = new HashMap<>();
893                 // traverse CFG...
894                 for (AbstractCfgNode cfgNodeX : userFunction.getControlFlowGraph().dfPreOrder()) {
895                     if (!(cfgNodeX instanceof Global)) {
896                         // we are only interested in "global" statements
897                         continue;
898                     }
899                     Global cfgNode = (Global) cfgNodeX;
900                     String varName = cfgNode.getOperand().getName();
901                     Variable correspondingGlobal = this.mainFunctionSymbolTable.getVariable(varName);
902     
903                     if (correspondingGlobal == null) {
904                         if (this.superglobalsSymbolTable.getVariable(varName) != null) {
905                             // this is bad programming practice: the programmer has
906                             // declared a superglobal as "global"; nothing to do here
907                         } else {
908                             // this means that there is a "global" declaration, but
909                             // the corresponding global variable has not been created;
910                             // happens here, for example:
911                             // global ${$foo['bar']}
912                             // reason for this strange syntax: there doesn't seem to
913                             // be an easier way to declare array elements as global;
914     
915                             // simply ignore for now
916                         }
917                     } else {
918                         declaredAsGlobal.put(varName, correspondingGlobal);
919                     }
920                 }
921     
922                 // replacement *******
923     
924                 // traverse CFG...
925                 for (AbstractCfgNode cfgNode : userFunction.getControlFlowGraph().dfPreOrder()) {
926                     // nothing to do for "global" statements
927                     if (cfgNode instanceof Global) {
928                         continue;
929                     }
930     
931                     // inspect this node's variables...
932                     int varCount = -1;
933                     for (Variable var : cfgNode.getVariables()) {
934                         varCount++;
935     
936                         // nothing to do for placeholders
937                         if (var == null) {
938                             continue;
939                         }
940     
941                         // if the name of the inspected variable matches the name of
942                         // one of the variables that have been declared "global":
943                         // raplace
944                         Variable theGlobal = declaredAsGlobal.get(var.getName());
945                         if (theGlobal != null) {
946                             //System.out.println("at: " + cfgNode.getClass() + ", " + cfgNode.getOriginalLineNumber());
947                             //System.out.println("replacing: " + var);
948                             //System.out.println("with: " + theGlobal);
949                             cfgNode.replaceVariable(varCount, theGlobal);
950                         }
951     
952                         // TODO: also consider the case that the inspected variable is
953                         // an array element of some variable that has been declared
954                         // "global"; also see above!
955                     }
956                 }
957             }
958         }

960         private Variable makePlace(String varName, SymbolTable symbolTable) {
961             // lookup variable in given symbol table
962             Variable variable = symbolTable.getVariable(varName);
963     
964             // if it isn't there: lookup variable in superglobals symbol table
965             if (variable == null) {
966                 variable = this.superglobalsSymbolTable.getVariable(varName);
967             }
968     
969             // if it isn't there either: add it to the given symbol table
970             if (variable == null) {
971                 variable = new Variable(varName, symbolTable);
972                 symbolTable.add(variable);
973             }
974     
975             // if it is created for the superglobalsSymbolTable, it has to be a superglobal
976             if (symbolTable == this.superglobalsSymbolTable) {
977                 variable.setIsSuperGlobal(true);
978             }
979     
980             // return place for the variable
981             return variable;
982         }

986             return this.makePlace(varName, this.functionStack.getLast().getSymbolTable());

1019         private static void connect(AbstractCfgNode source, AbstractCfgNode dest, int edgeType) {
1020             if (edgeType != CfgEdge.NO_EDGE) {
1021                 // create edge
1022                 CfgEdge edge = new CfgEdge(source, dest, edgeType);
1023     
1024                 // add outgoing edge to source node
1025                 if (edgeType == CfgEdge.TRUE_EDGE) {
1026                     source.setOutEdge(1, edge);
1027                 } else {
1028                     source.setOutEdge(0, edge);
1029                 }
1030     
1031                 // add incoming edge to destination node
1032                 dest.addInEdge(edge);
1033             }
1034         }

1036         static void connect(AbstractCfgNode source, AbstractCfgNode dest) {
1037             connect(source, dest, CfgEdge.NORMAL_EDGE);
1038         }

1065         // adds a method to this.userMethods; if a method with this methodName and
1066         // className already exists, it returns the already existing method;
1067         // otherwise, it adds the method and returns null
1068         private TacFunction addMethod(String methodName, String className, TacFunction method) {
1069             Map<String, TacFunction> class2Method = this.userMethods.get(methodName);
1070             if (class2Method == null) {
1071                 class2Method = new HashMap<>();
1072                 this.userMethods.put(methodName, class2Method);
1073             }
1074             TacFunction existingMethod = class2Method.get(className);
1075             if (existingMethod != null) {
1076                 return existingMethod;
1077             } else {
1078                 class2Method.put(className, method);
1079                 return null;
1080             }
1081         }

1089                 return null;
1090             }
1091             return class2Method.get(className);
1092         }

1103         // handles short-circuit code for AND, &&, OR, ||
1104         void booleanHelper(ParseNode node, TacAttributes myAtts, int type) {
1105     
1106             // short-circuit is taken into account...
1107             //
1108             // don't forget that the logical operators ("and", "or") have a very
1109             // low priority:
1110             // "$c =  $a and $b " is different from
1111             // "$c =  $a &&  $b " is equivalent to
1112             // "$c = ($a and $b)"
1113     
1114             Variable myPlace = newTemp();
1115     
1116             TacAttributes atts0 = this.expr(node.getChild(0));
1117             TacAttributes atts2 = this.expr(node.getChild(2));
1118     
1119             // nodes for assigning true or false to the temporary
1120             AbstractCfgNode trueNode = new AssignSimple(myPlace, Constant.TRUE, node);
1121             AbstractCfgNode falseNode = new AssignSimple(myPlace, Constant.FALSE, node);
1122     
1123             // target node for trueNode and falseNode
1124             AbstractCfgNode emptyNode = new Empty();
1125             connect(trueNode, emptyNode);
1126             connect(falseNode, emptyNode);
1127     
1128             // test for first expression
1129             AbstractCfgNode ifNode0 = new If(
1130                 atts0.getPlace(),
1131                 Constant.TRUE,
1132                 TacOperators.IS_EQUAL,
1133                 node.getChild(0));
1134     
1135             // test for second expression
1136             AbstractCfgNode ifNode2 = new If(
1137                 atts2.getPlace(),
1138                 Constant.TRUE,
1139                 TacOperators.IS_EQUAL,
1140                 node.getChild(2));
1141     
1142             // expr0's code comes before its test
1143             connect(atts0.getControlFlowGraph(), ifNode0);
1144     
1145             // expr2's code comes before the test
1146             connect(atts2.getControlFlowGraph(), ifNode2);
1147     
1148             if (type == PhpSymbols.T_LOGICAL_OR) {
1149                 // OR, ||
1150     
1151                 // if first test succeeds: done, true!
1152                 connect(ifNode0, trueNode, CfgEdge.TRUE_EDGE);
1153     
1154                 // if first test doesn't succeed: evaluate expr2
1155                 connect(ifNode0, atts2.getControlFlowGraph(), CfgEdge.FALSE_EDGE);
1156     
1157                 // if second test succeeds: done, true!
1158                 connect(ifNode2, trueNode, CfgEdge.TRUE_EDGE);
1159     
1160                 // if second test doesn't succeed: done, false!
1161                 connect(ifNode2, falseNode, CfgEdge.FALSE_EDGE);
1162             } else {
1163                 // AND, &&
1164     
1165                 // if test succeeds: evaluate expr2
1166                 connect(ifNode0, atts2.getControlFlowGraph(), CfgEdge.TRUE_EDGE);
1167     
1168                 // if test doesn't succeed: done, false!
1169                 connect(ifNode0, falseNode, CfgEdge.FALSE_EDGE);
1170     
1171                 // if test succeeds: done, true!
1172                 connect(ifNode2, trueNode, CfgEdge.TRUE_EDGE);
1173     
1174                 // if test doesn't succeed: done, false!
1175                 connect(ifNode2, falseNode, CfgEdge.FALSE_EDGE);
1176             }
1177     
1178             myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
1179                 atts0.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
1180                 emptyNode));
1181             myAtts.setPlace(myPlace);
1182         }

1184         // expression operator expression
1185         void expOpExp(ParseNode node, int op, TacAttributes myAtts) {
1186             Variable myPlace = null;
1187             int logId = this.tempId;
1188     
1189             TacAttributes atts0 = this.expr(node.getChild(0));
1190             // if the first expression has been stored to a temporary variable,
1191             // this variable can be reused
1192             if (atts0.getPlace().isVariable() && ((Variable) atts0.getPlace()).isTemp()) {
1193                 myPlace = (Variable) atts0.getPlace();
1194                 // update logId so that the next call to resetId will
1195                 // leave tempId higher than myPlace's
1196                 logId = this.tempId;
1197             } else {
1198                 this.resetId(logId);
1199             }
1200     
1201             TacAttributes atts2 = this.expr(node.getChild(2));
1202             // if we are still trying to reuse
1203             if (myPlace == null) {
1204                 if (atts2.getPlace().isVariable() && ((Variable) atts2.getPlace()).isTemp()) {
1205                     myPlace = (Variable) atts2.getPlace();
1206                 } else {
1207                     this.resetId(logId);
1208                     myPlace = this.newTemp();
1209                 }
1210             } else {
1211                 this.resetId(logId);
1212             }
1213     
1214             AbstractCfgNode cfgNode = new AssignBinary(
1215                 myPlace, atts0.getPlace(), atts2.getPlace(), op, node);
1216             connect(atts0.getControlFlowGraph(), atts2.getControlFlowGraph());
1217             connect(atts2.getControlFlowGraph(), cfgNode);
1218     
1219             myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(atts0.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(), cfgNode));
1220             myAtts.setPlace(myPlace);
1221         }

1224         void cvarOpExp(ParseNode node, int op, TacAttributes myAtts) {
1225     
1226             TacAttributes atts0 = this.cvar(node.getChild(0));

1235             myAtts.setPlace(atts0.getPlace());

1238         // post-increment and post-decrement
1239         void postIncDec(ParseNode node, int op, TacAttributes myAtts) {
1240             // temporary to rescue the variable's old value;
1241             // will be the expression's place
1242             Variable tempPlace = newTemp();
1243             TacAttributes atts0 = this.rw_cvar(node.getChild(0));
1244             AbstractTacPlace addMePlace = new Literal("1");
1245     
1246             // assign the variable's old value to the temporary
1247             AbstractCfgNode rescueNode = new AssignSimple(
1248                 tempPlace, atts0.getPlace(), node.getChild(0));
1249     
1250             // increment / decrement the variable
1251             AbstractCfgNode cfgNode = new AssignBinary(
1252                 (Variable) atts0.getPlace(), atts0.getPlace(), addMePlace, op, node);
1253     
1254             connect(atts0.getControlFlowGraph(), rescueNode);
1255             connect(rescueNode, cfgNode);
1256     
1257             myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(atts0.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(), cfgNode));
1258             myAtts.setPlace(tempPlace);
1259         }

1290         void functionHelper(ParseNode node, int paramListNum, int statNum, TacAttributes myAtts) {
1291             // LATER
1292             // - case: no return statement inside the function, but a caller uses
1293             //   the function's return value: probably a bug
1294             // - real-world effect in this case: the function returns the special
1295             //   value "NULL" (can be checked via var_dump())
1296             // - current implementation: the return value is TOP
1297             // - alternative, more exact implementation: assign the special value NULL
1298             //   to the functions return variable at the beginning of the function
1299     
1300             // name and referencedom
1301             String functionName = node.getChild(2).getLexeme().toLowerCase();
1302             boolean isReference = (node.getChild(1).getChild(0).getSymbol() == PhpSymbols.T_EPSILON);
1303     
1304             TacFunction existingFunction = this.userFunctions.get(functionName);
1305             if (existingFunction != null) {
1306     
1307                 // either a bug or a conditional function declaration
1308                 // approx: simply ignore this additional declaration
1309                 System.out.println("\nWarning: Duplicate function definition: " + functionName);
1310                 System.out.println("- found: " + node.getLoc());
1311                 System.out.println("- using: " + existingFunction.getLoc());
1312     
1313                 // return empty ControlFlowGraph (we don't put function Cfgs inside one another)
1314                 AbstractCfgNode emptyNode = new Empty();
1315                 myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(emptyNode, emptyNode));
1316                 return;
1317             }
1318     
1319             // the function's frame ControlFlowGraph
1320             CfgEntry entryNode = new CfgEntry(node);
1321             CfgExit exitNode = new CfgExit(node);
1322             ControlFlowGraph controlFlowGraph = new ControlFlowGraph(entryNode, exitNode, CfgEdge.NO_EDGE);
1323     
1324             // create function object
1325             TacFunction function = new TacFunction(
1326                 functionName,
1327                 controlFlowGraph,
1328                 this.makeReturnPlace(functionName),
1329                 isReference,
1330                 node, "");
1331             this.userFunctions.put(functionName, function);
1332     
1333             // push the function's name onto the function stack
1334             this.functionStack.add(function);
1335     
1336             // construct parameter list
1337             TacAttributes attsParamList = this.parameter_list(node.getChild(paramListNum));
1338     
1339             // for all formal parameters:
1340             // if this param has a default controlFlowGraph, inform all nodes of this default controlFlowGraph about
1341             // the entry node of the corresponding function
1342             for (TacFormalParameter formalParam : attsParamList.getFormalParamList()) {
1343                 if (formalParam.hasDefault()) {
1344                     ControlFlowGraph defaultControlFlowGraph = formalParam.getDefaultControlFlowGraph();
1345                     for (AbstractCfgNode defaultNode : defaultControlFlowGraph.dfPreOrder()) {
1346                         defaultNode.setDefaultParamPrep(entryNode);
1347                     }
1348                 }
1349             }
1350     
1351             // set function parameters
1352             function.setParams(attsParamList.getFormalParamList());
1353     
1354             // construct inner ControlFlowGraph
1355             TacAttributes attsStat = this.inner_statement_list(node.getChild(statNum));
1356     
1357             // embed inner ControlFlowGraph into function's frame ControlFlowGraph
1358             connect(entryNode, attsStat.getControlFlowGraph());
1359             connect(attsStat.getControlFlowGraph(), exitNode);
1360     
1361             // return empty ControlFlowGraph (we don't put function Cfgs inside one another)
1362             AbstractCfgNode emptyNode = new Empty();
1363             myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(emptyNode, emptyNode));
1364     
1365             // pop function stack
1366             this.functionStack.removeLast();
1367     
1368             // optimize function's ControlFlowGraph
1369             this.removeEmptyNodesFromCfg(controlFlowGraph);
1370         }

1451         // generate shadow variables for every function in this.userFunctions
1452         public void generateShadows() {
1453             for (TacFunction userFunction : this.userFunctions.values()) {
1454                 if (userFunction.isMain()) {
1455                     continue;   // skip the main function
1456                 }
1457                 this.generateShadows(userFunction);
1458             }

1461         // generates shadow variables for the given function;
1462         // don't call this function before calling transformGlobals(), otherwise
1463         // you will miss some g-shadows
1464         private void generateShadows(TacFunction function) {
1465             SymbolTable symTab = function.getSymbolTable();
1466     
1467             // G-SHADOWS
1468     
1469             // for each variable in the main function...
1470             for (Variable var : this.mainFunctionSymbolTable.getVariablesColl()) {
1471                 // no need to create shadows for temporaries
1472                 // [what about arrays and array elements?]
1473                 if (var.isTemp()) {
1474                     continue;
1475                 }
1476                 symTab.addGShadow(var);
1477             }
1478     
1479             // F-SHADOWS
1480     
1481             // for each formal parameter of this function...
1482             for (TacFormalParameter param : function.getParams()) {
1483                 Variable var = param.getVariable();
1484                 // no need to create shadows for arrays and array elements
1485                 if (var.isArray() || var.isArrayElement()) {
1486                     continue;
1487                 }
1488                 symTab.addFShadow(var);
1489             }
1490         }

1492         // constructs a sub-cfg for a function call and returns it;
1493         // if "backpatch" is set to false, "function" must be non-null
1494         // (since otherwise, there would be no call to the nodes' setFunction();
1495         // calledFuncName: name of the called function or method (must not be null)
1496         // isMethod:       is this a method call? (or a function call?)
1497         // calledFunction: object of the called function
1498         //                 (either this.someMethod or this.unknownFunction or null)
1499         ControlFlowGraph functionCallHelper(
1500             String calledFuncName, boolean isMethod, TacFunction calledFunction, List<TacActualParameter> paramList,
1501             AbstractTacPlace tempPlace, boolean backpatch, ParseNode parseNode, String className,
1502             Variable object) {
1503     
1504             // if this is a call to the "define" function, we return a one-node cfg
1505             // containing only the special define node
1506             if (calledFuncName.equals("define")) {
1507     
1508                 // extract params
1509                 Iterator<TacActualParameter> paramIter = paramList.iterator();
1510                 AbstractTacPlace setMe = paramIter.next().getPlace();
1511                 AbstractTacPlace setTo = paramIter.next().getPlace();
1512                 AbstractTacPlace caseInsensitive;
1513                 if (paramIter.hasNext()) {
1514                     caseInsensitive = paramIter.next().getPlace();
1515                 } else {
1516                     // default value for the third parameter
1517                     caseInsensitive = Constant.FALSE;
1518                 }
1519     
1520                 // if the defined constant is literal here, we can try to add
1521                 // it to the constants table
1522                 if (setMe.isLiteral()) {
1523                     this.makeConstantPlace(setMe.toString());
1524                 }
1525     
1526                 Define defineNode = new Define(
1527                     setMe, setTo, caseInsensitive, parseNode);
1528                 return new ControlFlowGraph(defineNode, defineNode);
1529             }
1530     
1531             // if this is a call to a builtin function, we return a one-node cfg
1532             // containing only the special "builtin call" node
1533             if (BuiltinFunctions.isBuiltinFunction(calledFuncName)) {
1534                 CallBuiltinFunction builtinNode =
1535                     new CallBuiltinFunction(calledFuncName, paramList, tempPlace, parseNode);
1536                 return new ControlFlowGraph(builtinNode, builtinNode);
1537             }
1538     
1539             Literal funcNameLit = new Literal(calledFuncName);
1540             Variable returnVariable = this.makeReturnPlace(calledFuncName);
1541     
1542             TacFunction enclosingFunction = this.functionStack.getLast();
1543     
1544             // create nodes
1545             CallPreparation prep = new CallPreparation(parseNode);
1546             Call call = new Call(
1547                 funcNameLit, calledFunction, parseNode, enclosingFunction,
1548                 returnVariable, tempPlace, paramList, object);
1549             CallReturn callRet = new CallReturn(parseNode);
1550     
1551             // connect nodes
1552             connect(prep, call);
1553             connect(call, callRet);
1554     
1555             // update backpatching list (if necessary)
1556             if (backpatch) {
1557                 if (isMethod) {
1558                     this.addMethodCall(enclosingFunction, prep);
1559                     call.setCalleeClassName(className);
1560                 } else {
1561                     this.addFunctionCall(enclosingFunction, prep);
1562                 }
1563             }
1564     
1565             return new ControlFlowGraph(prep, callRet);
1566         }

1622         // explicitly adds pre-defined elements of the
1623         // superglobal $_SERVER and $HTTP_SERVER_VARS arrays
1624         public void addSuperGlobalElements() {
1625             String[] indices = {
1626                 "PHP_SELF", "SERVER_NAME", "HTTP_HOST", "HTTP_REFERER",
1627                 "HTTP_ACCEPT_LANGUAGE", "SERVER_SOFTWARE", "PHP_AUTH_USER",
1628                 "PHP_AUTH_PW", "PHP_AUTH_TYPE", "SCRIPT_NAME", "SCRIPT_FILENAME",
1629                 "REQUEST_URI", "QUERY_STRING", "SCRIPT_URI"
1630             };
1631     
1632             // *** $_SERVER[...] ***
1633     
1634             String superName = "$_SERVER";
1635             Variable superVar = this.superglobalsSymbolTable.getVariable(superName);
1636             Variable var = null;
1637             for (String indice : indices) {
1638                 // only add the variable if it does not exist yet
1639                 var = this.superglobalsSymbolTable.getVariable(superName + "[" + indice + "]");
1640                 if (var == null) {
1641                     this.makeArrayElementPlace(superVar, new Literal(indice));
1642                 }
1643             }
1644     
1645             // LATER: not so elegant...
1646             Variable argv = this.superglobalsSymbolTable.getVariable(superName + "[argv]");
1647             if (argv == null) {
1648                 argv = this.makeArrayElementPlace(superVar, new Literal("argv"));
1649             }
1650             var = this.superglobalsSymbolTable.getVariable(superName + "[argv][0]");
1651             if (var == null) {
1652                 this.makeArrayElementPlace(argv, new Literal("0"));
1653             }
1654     
1655             // LATER: eliminate redundancy
1656             // *** $HTTP_SERVER_VARS[...] ***
1657     
1658             superName = "$HTTP_SERVER_VARS";
1659             superVar = this.superglobalsSymbolTable.getVariable(superName);
1660             for (String indice : indices) {
1661                 // only add the variable if it does not exist yet
1662                 var = this.superglobalsSymbolTable.getVariable(superName + "[" + indice + "]");
1663                 if (var == null) {
1664                     this.makeArrayElementPlace(superVar, new Literal(indice));
1665                 }
1666             }
1667     
1668             argv = this.superglobalsSymbolTable.getVariable(superName + "[argv]");
1669             if (argv == null) {
1670                 argv = this.makeArrayElementPlace(superVar, new Literal("argv"));
1671             }
1672             var = this.superglobalsSymbolTable.getVariable(superName + "[argv][0]");
1673             if (var == null) {
1674                 this.makeArrayElementPlace(argv, new Literal("0"));
1675             }
1676         }

1678         // - marks the enclosing array as array
1679         // - determines if the enclosing array is superglobal or not
1680         // - creates the array element and sets its properties
1681         // - informs the enclosing array about the element
1682         Variable makeArrayElementPlace(AbstractTacPlace arrayPlace, AbstractTacPlace offsetPlace) {
1683             // the enclosing array
1684             Variable arrayVar = arrayPlace.getVariable();
1685             // mark it as array
1686             if (!arrayVar.isArray()) {
1687                 arrayVar.setIsArray(true);
1688             }
1689             String offsetString = offsetPlace.toString();
1690     
1691             // if the enclosing array is superglobal, then the array
1692             // element is superglobal as well
1693             boolean superGlobal;
1694             SymbolTable symbolTable;
1695             if (arrayVar.isSuperGlobal()) {
1696                 symbolTable = this.superglobalsSymbolTable;
1697                 superGlobal = true;
1698             } else {
1699                 symbolTable = this.functionStack.getLast().getSymbolTable();
1700                 superGlobal = false;
1701             }
1702     
1703             // name for the array element
1704             String arrayElementName = arrayVar.getName() + "[" + offsetString + "]";
1705     
1706             // look if the array element already exists; we only have to do more work
1707             // if it hasn't been created yet
1708             Variable arrayElementVar = symbolTable.getVariable(arrayElementName);
1709             if (arrayElementVar == null) {
1710     
1711                 // add it to the symbol table
1712                 arrayElementVar = new Variable(arrayElementName, symbolTable);
1713                 symbolTable.add(arrayElementVar);
1714     
1715                 // set array element attributes
1716                 arrayElementVar.setArrayElementAttributes(
1717                     arrayVar, offsetPlace);
1718                 arrayElementVar.setIsSuperGlobal(superGlobal);
1719     
1720                 // inform enclosing array about the element
1721                 arrayVar.addElement(arrayElementVar);
1722             }
1723     
1724             return arrayElementVar;
1725         }

1727         // - creates the array element and
1728         //   creates a ControlFlowGraph node which either assigns a value to the array element
1729         //   or makes the array element a reference to the given valuePlace
1730         AbstractCfgNode arrayPairListHelper(
1731             AbstractTacPlace arrayPlace, AbstractTacPlace offsetPlace, AbstractTacPlace valuePlace,
1732             boolean reference, ParseNode node) {
1733     
1734             Variable arrayElementPlace = this.makeArrayElementPlace(arrayPlace, offsetPlace);
1735     
1736             // assign value to array element or create reference
1737             if (reference) {
1738                 return (new AssignReference(arrayElementPlace, (Variable) valuePlace, node));
1739             } else {
1740                 return (new AssignSimple(arrayElementPlace, valuePlace, node));
1741             }
1742         }

1755         // returns the right place for
1756         // $ { expr }
1757         // no matter if it is encountered within double quotes or not
1758         AbstractTacPlace exprVarHelper(AbstractTacPlace exprPlace) {
1759             AbstractTacPlace myPlace = null;
1760             if (exprPlace.isLiteral()) {
1761                 // intended transformations for literals:
1762                 // ${'123'}  -->  ${'123'}
1763                 // ${'1xy'}  -->  ${'1xy'}
1764                 // ${'foo'}  -->  $foo
1765                 // ${123}    -->  ${'123'}
1766                 // ${1xy}    -->  syntax error
1767                 // ${foo}    -->  $foo      // means that we are inside double quotes*
1768                 //
1769                 // *since otherwise we would not be inside the "literal" branch,
1770                 //  but inside the "constant" branch below
1771                 //
1772                 // no need to set dependency relation here
1773     
1774                 String literal = exprPlace.toString();
1775     
1776                 if (Character.isDigit(literal.charAt(0))) {
1777                     myPlace = this.makePlace("${" + literal + "}");
1778                 } else {
1779                     myPlace = this.makePlace("$" + literal);
1780                 }
1781             } else if (exprPlace.isVariable()) {
1782                 myPlace = this.makePlace("${" + exprPlace.getVariable().getName() + "}");
1783                 myPlace.getVariable().setDependsOn(exprPlace);
1784             } else if (exprPlace.isConstant()) {
1785                 myPlace = this.makePlace("${" + exprPlace.getConstant().getLabel() + "}");
1786                 myPlace.getVariable().setDependsOn(exprPlace);
1787             } else {
1788                 throw new RuntimeException("SNH");
1789             }
1790     
1791             return myPlace;
1792         }

1794         // attsArray: the array to be run through ($arr in the example below)
1795         private void foreachHelper(ParseNode node, TacAttributes attsArray, TacAttributes myAtts) {
1796             // translation of
1797             //
1798             // foreach ($arr AS [$key =>] $value) {...}
1799             //
1800             // must have the same result as the translation of
1801             //
1802             // reset($arr);
1803             // while (list([$key], $value) = each($arr)) {...}
1804     
1805             // copy the array into a temporary to ensure correct semantics
1806             Variable arrayPlace = this.newTemp();
1807             AbstractCfgNode backupNode = new AssignSimple(arrayPlace, attsArray.getPlace(), node);
1808     
1809             // create nodes for calls to reset() and each()
1810             List<TacActualParameter> paramList = new LinkedList<>();
1811             paramList.add(new TacActualParameter(arrayPlace, false));
1812             int logId = this.tempId;
1813             // place for the array returned by each(); can also be used
1814             // for reset() since we don't need its return value
1815             AbstractTacPlace tempPlace = this.newTemp();
1816     
1817             ControlFlowGraph resetCallControlFlowGraph = this.functionCallHelper(
1818                 "reset", false, null, paramList,
1819                 tempPlace, true, node, null, null);
1820     
1821             ControlFlowGraph eachCallControlFlowGraph = this.functionCallHelper(
1822                 "each", false, null, paramList,
1823                 tempPlace, true, node, null, null);
1824     
1825             connect(attsArray.getControlFlowGraph(), backupNode);
1826             connect(backupNode, resetCallControlFlowGraph.getHead());
1827             connect(resetCallControlFlowGraph.getTail(), eachCallControlFlowGraph.getHead());
1828     
1829             // node testing whether to stay inside the loop or not
1830             AbstractCfgNode ifNode = new If(
1831                 tempPlace,
1832                 Constant.TRUE,
1833                 TacOperators.IS_EQUAL,
1834                 node);
1835     
1836             // end node for the whole foreach construct
1837             AbstractCfgNode endNode = new Empty();
1838     
1839             // assigning the array returned by each() to the right variables
1840             TacAttributes attsOptional = this.foreach_optional_arg(node.getChild(5));
1841             // we need to distinguish whether there is a "foreach_optional_arg" or
1842             // not (i.e. if there is a "=> w_cvar" or not)
1843             if (attsOptional == null) {
1844     
1845                 // there is no foreach_optional_arg, which means that there is
1846                 // only a value (instead of key => value)
1847     
1848                 TacAttributes attsValue = this.w_cvar(node.getChild(4));
1849     
1850                 AbstractTacPlace tempPlaceValue = this.makeArrayElementPlace(
1851                     tempPlace, new Literal("1"));
1852     
1853                 AbstractCfgNode valueNode = new AssignSimple(
1854                     (Variable) attsValue.getPlace(), tempPlaceValue, node.getChild(4));
1855     
1856                 connect(eachCallControlFlowGraph.getTail(), attsValue.getControlFlowGraph());
1857                 connect(attsValue.getControlFlowGraph(), valueNode);
1858                 connect(valueNode, ifNode);
1859             } else {
1860     
1861                 // there is a foreach_optional_arg, which means that there
1862                 // is a "key => value" mapping
1863     
1864                 TacAttributes attsKey = this.w_cvar(node.getChild(4));
1865                 TacAttributes attsValue = attsOptional;
1866     
1867                 AbstractTacPlace tempPlaceKey = this.makeArrayElementPlace(
1868                     tempPlace, new Literal("0"));
1869                 AbstractTacPlace tempPlaceValue = this.makeArrayElementPlace(
1870                     tempPlace, new Literal("1"));
1871     
1872                 AbstractCfgNode keyNode = new AssignSimple(
1873                     (Variable) attsKey.getPlace(), tempPlaceKey, node.getChild(4));
1874     
1875                 AbstractCfgNode valueNode = new AssignSimple(
1876                     (Variable) attsValue.getPlace(), tempPlaceValue, node.getChild(5));
1877     
1878                 connect(eachCallControlFlowGraph.getTail(), attsKey.getControlFlowGraph());
1879                 connect(attsKey.getControlFlowGraph(), attsValue.getControlFlowGraph());
1880                 connect(attsValue.getControlFlowGraph(), keyNode);
1881                 connect(keyNode, valueNode);
1882                 connect(valueNode, ifNode);
1883             }
1884     
1885             this.resetId(logId);
1886     
1887             // prepare break and continue stacks for loop body
1888             this.continueTargetStack.add(eachCallControlFlowGraph.getHead());
1889             this.breakTargetStack.add(endNode);
1890     
1891             // loop body
1892             TacAttributes attsStatement = this.foreach_statement(node.getChild(7));
1893             connect(ifNode, attsStatement.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(), CfgEdge.TRUE_EDGE);
1894             // DON'T use this to connect the loop body to the loop header:
1895             // if the loop body contains a return statement, it won't lead to the
1896             // function's exit node this way!
1897             //connect(attsStatement.getControlFlowGraph().getTail(), eachCallControlFlowGraph.getHead());
1898             // use the following line instead:
1899             connect(attsStatement.getControlFlowGraph(), eachCallControlFlowGraph.getHead());
1900             connect(ifNode, endNode, CfgEdge.FALSE_EDGE);
1901     
1902             this.continueTargetStack.removeLast();
1903             this.breakTargetStack.removeLast();
1904     
1905             myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(attsArray.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(), endNode));
1906         }
1907     
1908         // preliminary backpatching
1909         public void backpatch() {
1910             backpatch(false, false, null, null);
1911         }
