1913         // backpatching for function calls
1914         // - riskMethods: perform method disambiguation based on method name?
1915         //   only do this if there will be no further file inclusions
1916         // - finalPass: issues warnings for unresolved calls, and performs some
1917         //   source code replacements
1918         // - typeAnalysis: can also be null
1919         public void backpatch(boolean riskMethods, boolean finalPass, TypeAnalysis typeAnalysis, CallGraph callGraph) {
1920             // method backpatching
1921             for (List<CallPreparation> callList : this.methodCalls.values()) {
1922                 for (CallPreparation prepNode : callList) {
1923     
1924                     Call callNode = prepNode.getCallNode();
1925                     CallReturn retNode = prepNode.getCallRetNode();
1926     
1927                     // determine reachability of this call node
1928                     boolean reachable = true;
1929                     TacFunction enclosingFunction = callNode.getEnclosingFunction();
1930                     if (callGraph != null) {
1931                         if (!callGraph.reachable(enclosingFunction)) {
1932                             reachable = false;
1933                         }
1934                     }
1935     
1936                     AbstractTacPlace functionNamePlace = prepNode.getFunctionNamePlace();
1937     
1938                     // note: only methods with literal names have been added to the backpatching list
1939     
1940                     // note: if some called function or method can't be found, it could
1941                     // be because the node that includes the file containing this function
1942                     // is unreachable (e.g., the node is inside a function that is never
1943                     // called); this can be identified by inspecting the call graph (dumped in
1944                     // calledby.txt); in such cases, the warning can be ignored;
1945     
1946                     // try to retrieve the callee...
1947     
1948                     TacFunction callee = null;
1949                     Map<String, TacFunction> class2Method = this.userMethods.get(functionNamePlace.toString());
1950     
1951                     // only if we have a class2Method mapping for this method name, there is
1952                     // a chance that we can retrieve the callee method; otherwise, it means that
1953                     // have haven't found a method definition with this name anywhere
1954                     if (class2Method != null) {
1955                         String calleeClassName = callNode.getCalleeClassName();
1956     
1957                         if (calleeClassName != null) {
1958                             // we know the class to which the called method belongs, so we
1959                             // can try to retrieve the corresponding method
1960                             callee = class2Method.get(calleeClassName);
1961                         } else if (riskMethods) {
1962                             // we don't know the class to which the called method belongs, so
1963                             // we hope that there is only one method with this name;
1964                             // only do this during the final pass, since you can get strange
1965                             // effects otherwise (e.g.: a class with an appropriate method name
1966                             // is included first, but this method is not called in reality; in
1967                             // a later inclusion pass, the real method is included...)
1968                             if (class2Method.size() == 1) {
1969                                 callee = class2Method.values().iterator().next();
1970                             } else {
1971                                 // there is more than one method with this name, so
1972                                 // which one should we take?
1973                                 boolean resolved = false;
1974     
1975                                 // try to ask type analysis
1976                                 if (typeAnalysis != null) {
1977                                     Set<Type> types = typeAnalysis.getType(callNode.getObject(), callNode);
1978                                     if (types != null && types.size() == 1) {
1979                                         // resolved it!
1980                                         Type type = types.iterator().next();
1981                                         callee = class2Method.get(type.getClassName());
1982                                         if (callee != null) {
1983                                             resolved = true;
1984                                         } else {
1985                                             // type analysis has made a mistake
1986                                         }
1987                                     }
1988                                 }
1989     
1990                                 // if we have left it unresolved...
1991                                 if (finalPass && !resolved && reachable) {
1992                                     System.out.println("reachable: " + enclosingFunction.getName());
1993                                     System.out.println("Warning: can't resolve method call (same name in different classes)");
1994                                     System.out.println("- name:    " + functionNamePlace);
1995                                     System.out.println("- call:    " + prepNode.getLoc());
1996                                     System.out.println("- classes: " + class2Method.keySet());
1997                                 }
1998                             }
1999                         }
2000                     } else {
2001                         if (finalPass && reachable) {
2002                             System.out.println("Warning: can't resolve method call (no definition found)");
2003                             System.out.println("- name:    " + functionNamePlace);
2004                             System.out.println("- call:    " + prepNode.getLoc());
2005                         }
2006                     }
2007     
2008                     if (callee == null) {
2009                         if (finalPass) {
2010                             // replace the three call nodes with a cfgnodecallunknown
2011                             this.replaceUnknownCall(prepNode, functionNamePlace.toString(), true);
2012                         }
2013                         continue;
2014                     } else {
2015                         List<TacActualParameter> actualParams = prepNode.getParamList();
2016                         List<TacFormalParameter> formalParams = callee.getParams();
2017                         int actualSize = actualParams.size();
2018                         int formalSize = formalParams.size();
2019                         if (actualSize != formalSize) {
2020                             if (actualSize > formalSize) {
2021                                 // more actual than formal params; either a bug or a
2022                                 // varargs occurrence; LATER: think about this;
2023                                 // for now: delete additional params
2024                                 System.out.println("Warning: More actual than formal params");
2025                                 System.out.println("- call:    " + prepNode.getLoc());
2026                                 System.out.println("- callee:  " + prepNode.getFunctionNamePlace().toString());
2027                                 System.out.println("- decl:    " + callee.getLoc());
2028                                 while (actualParams.size() > formalParams.size()) {
2029                                     actualParams.remove(actualParams.size() - 1);
2030                                 }
2031                             } else {
2032                                 // more formal than actual params;
2033                                 // this is only ok if the missing actuals are matched by
2034                                 // default formals; otherwise, it is a bug
2035     
2036                                 if (finalPass) {
2037                                     // find out if this is a bug
2038                                     int i = 0;
2039                                     for (TacFormalParameter formalParam : formalParams) {
2040                                         i++;
2041                                         if (i <= actualSize) {
2042                                             continue;
2043                                         }
2044                                         if (!formalParam.hasDefault()) {
2045                                             System.out.println("Warning: Not enough actual params");
2046                                             System.out.println("- call:    " + prepNode.getLoc());
2047                                             System.out.println("- callee:  " + prepNode.getFunctionNamePlace().toString());
2048                                             System.out.println("- decl:    " + callee.getLoc());
2049                                             break;
2050                                         }
2051                                     }
2052                                 }
2053                             }
2054                         }
2055                     }
2056     
2057                     callNode.setCallee(callee);
2058                     retNode.setRetVar(callee.getRetVar());
2059                 }
2060             }
2061     
2062             // function backpatching
2063             for (List<CallPreparation> callList : this.functionCalls.values()) {
2064                 for (CallPreparation prepNode : callList) {
2065     
2066                     Call callNode = prepNode.getCallNode();
2067                     CallReturn retNode = (CallReturn) callNode.getOutEdge(0).getDestination();
2068     
2069                     AbstractTacPlace functionNamePlace = prepNode.getFunctionNamePlace();
2070     
2071                     // determine reachability of this call node
2072                     boolean reachable = true;
2073                     if (callGraph != null) {
2074                         TacFunction enclosingFunction = callNode.getEnclosingFunction();
2075                         if (!callGraph.reachable(enclosingFunction)) {
2076                             reachable = false;
2077                         }
2078                     }
2079     
2080                     // only functions with literal names have been added to the backpatching list;
2081                     // the others should be linked with their corresponding function objects
2082                     // (or the special _unknownFunction) by the CP
2083                     TacFunction callee = this.userFunctions.get(functionNamePlace.toString());
2084                     if (callee == null) {
2085                         if (BuiltinFunctions.isBuiltinFunction(functionNamePlace.toString())) {
2086                             // since we are now using a separate cfg node for calls to
2087                             // builtin functions, this case should not happen
2088                             throw new RuntimeException("SNH");
2089                         } else {
2090                             // not having information about a non-builtin function IS bad,
2091                             // since it could contain sensitive sinks
2092                             if (finalPass) {
2093                                 if (reachable) {
2094                                     System.out.println("Warning: can't find function " + functionNamePlace);
2095                                     System.out.println("- " + prepNode.getLoc());
2096                                 }
2097     
2098                                 // replace the three call nodes with a cfgnodecallunknown
2099                                 this.replaceUnknownCall(prepNode, functionNamePlace.toString(), false);
2100                             }
2101     
2102                             continue;
2103                         }
2104                     } else {
2105                         List<TacActualParameter> actualParams = prepNode.getParamList();
2106                         List<TacFormalParameter> formalParams = callee.getParams();
2107                         int actualSize = actualParams.size();
2108                         int formalSize = formalParams.size();
2109                         if (actualSize != formalSize) {
2110                             if (actualSize > formalSize) {
2111                                 // more actual than formal params; either a bug or a
2112                                 // varargs occurrence; LATER: think about this;
2113                                 // for now: delete additional params
2114                                 System.out.println("Warning: More actual than formal params");
2115                                 System.out.println("- call:    " + prepNode.getLoc());
2116                                 System.out.println("- callee:  " + prepNode.getFunctionNamePlace().toString());
2117                                 System.out.println("- decl:    " + callee.getLoc());
2118                                 while (actualParams.size() > formalParams.size()) {
2119                                     actualParams.remove(actualParams.size() - 1);
2120                                 }
2121                             } else {
2122                                 // more formal than actual params;
2123                                 // this is only ok if the missing actuals are matched by
2124                                 // default formals; otherwise, it is a bug
2125     
2126                                 if (finalPass) {
2127                                     // find out if this is a bug
2128                                     int i = 0;
2129                                     for (TacFormalParameter formalParam : formalParams) {
2130                                         i++;
2131                                         if (i <= actualSize) {
2132                                             continue;
2133                                         }
2134                                         if (!formalParam.hasDefault()) {
2135                                             System.out.println("Warning: Not enough actual params");
2136                                             System.out.println("- call:    " + prepNode.getLoc());
2137                                             System.out.println("- callee:  " + prepNode.getFunctionNamePlace().toString());
2138                                             System.out.println("- decl:    " + callee.getLoc());
2139                                             break;
2140                                         }
2141                                     }
2142                                 }
2143                             }
2144                         }
2145                     }
2146     
2147                     callNode.setCallee(callee);
2148                     retNode.setRetVar(callee.getRetVar());
2149                 }
2150             }
2151         }

2153         private void replaceUnknownCall(CallPreparation prepNode, String functionName, boolean isMethod) {
2154             CallReturn callRet = prepNode.getCallRetNode();
2155     
2156             // the replacement node
2157             CallUnknownFunction callUnknown = new CallUnknownFunction(
2158                 functionName,
2159                 prepNode.getParamList(),
2160                 callRet.getTempVar(),
2161                 prepNode.getParseNode(),
2162                 isMethod);
2163     
2164             // update predecessors:
2165             // redirect edges that enter the prep node
2166             for (CfgEdge inEdge : prepNode.getInEdges()) {
2167                 inEdge.setDestination(callUnknown);
2168                 callUnknown.addInEdge(inEdge);
2169             }
2170     
2171             // update successor
2172             List<AbstractCfgNode> succs = prepNode.getCallRetNode().getSuccessors();
2173             if (succs.size() == 1) {
2174                 AbstractCfgNode succ = succs.get(0);
2175                 succ.removeInEdge(callRet);
2176                 connect(callUnknown, succ);
2177             } else if (succs.size() == 0) {
2178                 // happens here, for instance:
2179                 // die(xyz());
2180             } else {
2181                 throw new RuntimeException("SNH");
2182             }
2183         }

2189         void start(ParseNode rootNode) {
2190             // always:
2191             // -> top_statement_list
2192     
2193             // entry and exit nodes for the (virtual) main mainFunction;
2194             // no need for a CfgNodeExitPrep here
2195             AbstractCfgNode entryNode = new CfgEntry(rootNode);
2196             AbstractCfgNode exitNode = new CfgExit(rootNode);
2197     
2198             // ControlFlowGraph for the main mainFunction
2199             ControlFlowGraph controlFlowGraph = new ControlFlowGraph(entryNode, exitNode, CfgEdge.NO_EDGE);
2200     
2201             // name of main mainFunction
2202             String mainFunctionName = InternalStrings.mainFunctionName;
2203     
2204             // mainFunction object
2205             TacFunction mainFunction = new TacFunction(
2206                 mainFunctionName,
2207                 controlFlowGraph,
2208                 this.makeReturnPlace(mainFunctionName),
2209                 false,
2210                 rootNode, "");
2211             // not necessary, but clean
2212             List<TacFormalParameter> l = Collections.emptyList();
2213             mainFunction.setParams(l);
2214             mainFunction.setIsMain(true);
2215     
2216             // add the mainFunction to the list of user functions
2217             this.userFunctions.put(mainFunctionName, mainFunction);
2218     
2219             // make shortcut to the main mainFunction
2220             this.mainFunction = mainFunction;
2221     
2222             // make shortcut to the symbol table of the main mainFunction
2223             this.mainFunctionSymbolTable = mainFunction.getSymbolTable();
2224     
2225             // push mainFunction onto the mainFunction stack
2226             this.functionStack.add(mainFunction);
2227     
2228             // descend into parse tree
2229             TacAttributes atts0 = this.top_statement_list(rootNode.getChild(0));
2230     
2231             // embed recursively constructed ControlFlowGraph into the mainFunction's frame ControlFlowGraph
2232             connect(entryNode, atts0.getControlFlowGraph());
2233             connect(atts0.getControlFlowGraph(), exitNode);
2234     
2235             this.functionStack.removeLast();
2236             this.removeEmptyNodesFromCfg(controlFlowGraph);
2237     
2238             // transform entries of the $GLOBALS array into corresponding
2239             // global variables (= local variables of the main mainFunction);
2240             // note: $GLOBALS-stuff can't be used for formal params, so it is
2241             // sufficient to traverse the CFG's
2242             for (TacFunction userFunction : this.userFunctions.values()) {
2243                 this.transformGlobals(userFunction.getControlFlowGraph());
2244             }
2245         }

2247         // - cfg
2248         TacAttributes top_statement_list(ParseNode node) {
2249             TacAttributes myAtts = new TacAttributes();
2250     
2251             ParseNode firstChild = node.getChild(0);
2252             switch (firstChild.getSymbol()) {
2253                 // -> top_statement_list top_statement
2254                 case PhpSymbols.top_statement_list: {
2255                     int logId = this.tempId;
2256                     TacAttributes atts0 = this.top_statement_list(firstChild);
2257                     TacAttributes atts1 = this.top_statement(node.getChild(1));
2258     
2259                     connect(atts0.getControlFlowGraph(), atts1.getControlFlowGraph());
2260                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
2261                         atts0.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
2262                         atts1.getControlFlowGraph().getTail(),
2263                         atts1.getControlFlowGraph().getTailEdgeType()));
2264                     this.resetId(logId);
2265                     break;
2266                 }
2267     
2268                 // -> empty
2269                 case PhpSymbols.T_EPSILON: {
2270                     AbstractCfgNode emptyNode = new Empty();
2271                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(emptyNode, emptyNode));
2272                     break;
2273                 }
2274             }
2275     
2276             return myAtts;
2277         }

2312         TacAttributes unticked_declaration_statement(ParseNode node) {
2313             TacAttributes myAtts = new TacAttributes();
2314     
2315             ParseNode fourthChild = node.getChild(3);
2316             switch (fourthChild.getSymbol()) {
2317     
2318                 // -> T_FUNCTION is_reference T_STRING ( parameter_list ) { inner_statement_list }
2319                 case PhpSymbols.T_OPEN_BRACES: {
2320                     this.functionHelper(node, 4, 7, myAtts);
2321                     break;
2322                 }
2323     
2324                 // -> T_OLD_FUNCTION is_reference T_STRING parameter_list ( inner_statement_list ) ;
2325                 case PhpSymbols.parameter_list: {
2326                     this.functionHelper(node, 3, 5, myAtts);
2327                     break;
2328                 }
2329     
2330                 // -> T_CLASS T_STRING { class_statement_list }
2331                 case PhpSymbols.class_statement_list: {
2332                     // collect information about the class and register
2333                     // the TacClass in userClasses
2334                     String className = node.getChild(1).getLexeme().toLowerCase();
2335                     TacClass c = new TacClass(className, node);
2336                     TacClass existingClass = this.userClasses.get(className);
2337                     if (existingClass == null) {
2338     
2339                         this.userClasses.put(className, c);
2340                         this.classStack.add(c);
2341                         this.class_statement_list(fourthChild, c);
2342                         this.classStack.removeLast();
2343     
2344                         // if this class does not explicitly define a constructor,
2345                         // add an empty one (makes things much easier)
2346                         String constructorName = className + InternalStrings.methodSuffix;
2347                         if (this.getMethod(constructorName, className) == null) {
2348     
2349                             TacFunction constructor = this.constructorHelper(node.getChild(0), className);
2350                             c.addMethod(constructorName, constructor);
2351     
2352                             // add this method to a global list of methods
2353                             TacFunction existingMethod = this.addMethod(constructorName, className, constructor);
2354                             if (existingMethod != null) {
2355                                 throw new RuntimeException("SNH");
2356                             }
2357                         }
2358                     } else {
2359                         System.out.println("\nWarning: Duplicate class definition: " + className);
2360                         System.out.println("- found: " + node.getLoc());
2361                         System.out.println("- using: " + existingClass.getLoc());
2362                     }
2363     
2364                     // put an empty node in place of class declarations
2365                     // (we don't need the declaration in the resulting cfg)
2366                     AbstractCfgNode emptyNode = new Empty();
2367                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(emptyNode, emptyNode));
2368                     break;
2369                 }
2370     
2371                 // -> T_CLASS T_STRING T_EXTENDS T_STRING { class_statement_list }
2372                 case PhpSymbols.T_STRING: {
2373                     // collect information about the class and register
2374                     // the TacClass in userClasses
2375                     String className = node.getChild(1).getLexeme().toLowerCase();
2376     
2377                     TacClass c = new TacClass(className, node);
2378                     TacClass existingClass = this.userClasses.get(className);
2379                     if (existingClass == null) {
2380     
2381                         this.userClasses.put(className, c);
2382                         this.classStack.add(c);
2383                         this.class_statement_list(node.getChild(5), c);
2384                         this.classStack.removeLast();
2385     
2386                         // if this class does not explicitly define a constructor,
2387                         // add an empty one (makes things much easier)
2388                         String constructorName = className + InternalStrings.methodSuffix;
2389                         if (this.getMethod(constructorName, className) == null) {
2390     
2391                             TacFunction constructor = this.constructorHelper(node.getChild(0), className);
2392                             c.addMethod(constructorName, constructor);
2393     
2394                             // add this method to a global list of methods
2395                             TacFunction existingMethod = this.addMethod(constructorName, className, constructor);
2396                             if (existingMethod != null) {
2397                                 throw new RuntimeException("SNH");
2398                             }
2399                         }
2400                     } else {
2401                         System.out.println("\nWarning: Duplicate class definition: " + className);
2402                         System.out.println("- found: " + node.getLoc());
2403                         System.out.println("- using: " + existingClass.getLoc());
2404                     }
2405     
2406                     // put an empty node in place of class declarations
2407                     // (we don't need the declaration in the resulting cfg)
2408                     AbstractCfgNode emptyNode = new Empty();
2409                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(emptyNode, emptyNode));

2494         TacAttributes class_variable_declaration(ParseNode node, TacClass c) {
2495             TacAttributes myAtts = new TacAttributes();
2496     
2497             ParseNode firstChild = node.getChild(0);
2498             switch (firstChild.getSymbol()) {
2499     
2500                 // -> class_variable_declaration ...
2501                 case PhpSymbols.class_variable_decleration: {
2502                     if (node.getNumChildren() == 3) {
2503                         // -> class_variable_declaration T_COMMA T_VARIABLE
2504                         this.class_variable_declaration(firstChild, c);
2505     
2506                         Variable var = this.newTemp();
2507                         AbstractCfgNode cfgNode = new AssignSimple(var, this.constantsTable.getConstant("NULL"), node);
2508                         ControlFlowGraph nullControlFlowGraph = new ControlFlowGraph(cfgNode, cfgNode);
2509                         c.addMember(node.getChild(2).getLexeme(), nullControlFlowGraph, var);
2510                     } else {
2511                         // -> class_variable_declaration T_COMMA T_VARIABLE T_ASSIGN static_scalar
2512                         this.class_variable_declaration(firstChild, c);
2513     
2514                         TacAttributes atts4 = this.static_scalar(node.getChild(4));
2515                         c.addMember(node.getChild(2).getLexeme(), atts4.getControlFlowGraph(), atts4.getPlace());
2516                     }
2517                     break;
2518                 }
2519     
2520                 // -> T_VARIABLE ...
2521                 case PhpSymbols.T_VARIABLE: {
2522                     if (node.getNumChildren() == 1) {
2523                         // -> T_VARIABLE
2524                         // create a one-node cfg that assigns NULL to a temporary variable,
2525                         // and use this cfg as initializer for the member variable
2526                         Variable var = this.newTemp();
2527                         AbstractCfgNode cfgNode = new AssignSimple(var, this.constantsTable.getConstant("NULL"), node);
2528                         ControlFlowGraph nullControlFlowGraph = new ControlFlowGraph(cfgNode, cfgNode);
2529                         c.addMember(firstChild.getLexeme(), nullControlFlowGraph, var);
2530                     } else {
2531                         // -> T_VARIABLE T_ASSIGN static_scalar
2532                         TacAttributes atts2 = this.static_scalar(node.getChild(2));
2533                         c.addMember(firstChild.getLexeme(), atts2.getControlFlowGraph(), atts2.getPlace());
2534                     }
2535                     break;
2536                 }
2537             }

2539             return myAtts;
2540         }

2713                     myAtts.setPlace(tempPlace);

2720                     TacAttributes atts1 = this.static_scalar(node.getChild(1));

2730                 case PhpSymbols.T_ARRAY: {

2733                         node.getChild(2),
2734                         arrayPlace);

2738

2929         // - cfg
2930         TacAttributes unticked_statement(ParseNode node) {
2931             TacAttributes myAtts = new TacAttributes();
2932     
2933             ParseNode firstChild = node.getChild(0);
2934             switch (firstChild.getSymbol()) {
2935     
2936                 // -> { inner_statement_list }
2937                 case PhpSymbols.T_OPEN_CURLY_BRACES: {
2938                     TacAttributes atts1 = this.inner_statement_list(node.getChild(1));
2939                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(atts1.getControlFlowGraph());
2940                     break;
2941                 }
2942     
2943                 // -> T_IF ( expr ) ...
2944                 case PhpSymbols.T_IF: {
2945                     if (node.getChild(4).getSymbol() == PhpSymbols.statement) {
2946                         // -> T_IF ( expr ) statement elseif_list else_single
2947     
2948                         AbstractCfgNode endIfNode = new Empty();
2949     
2950                         int logId = this.tempId;
2951                         TacAttributes attsExpr = this.expr(node.getChild(2));
2952                         this.resetId(logId);
2953                         TacAttributes attsStatement = this.statement(node.getChild(4));
2954                         TacAttributes attsElse = this.else_single(node.getChild(6));
2955                         TacAttributes attsElif = this.elseif_list(
2956                             node.getChild(5), endIfNode, attsElse.getControlFlowGraph().getHead());
2957     
2958                         AbstractCfgNode ifNode = new If(
2959                             attsExpr.getPlace(), Constant.TRUE, TacOperators.IS_EQUAL,
2960                             node.getChild(2));
2961     
2962                         connect(attsExpr.getControlFlowGraph(), ifNode);
2963                         connect(ifNode, attsElif.getControlFlowGraph(), CfgEdge.FALSE_EDGE);
2964                         connect(ifNode, attsStatement.getControlFlowGraph(), CfgEdge.TRUE_EDGE);
2965                         connect(attsStatement.getControlFlowGraph(), endIfNode);
2966                         connect(attsElse.getControlFlowGraph(), endIfNode);
2967     
2968                         myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
2969                             attsExpr.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
2970                             endIfNode));
2971                     } else {
2972                         // -> T_IF ( expr ) : inner_statement_list new_elseif_list
2973                         //    new_else_single T_ENDIF ;
2974     
2975                         AbstractCfgNode endIfNode = new Empty();
2976     
2977                         int logId = this.tempId;
2978                         TacAttributes attsExpr = this.expr(node.getChild(2));
2979                         this.resetId(logId);
2980                         TacAttributes attsStatement = this.inner_statement_list(node.getChild(5));
2981                         TacAttributes attsElse = this.new_else_single(node.getChild(7));
2982                         TacAttributes attsElif = this.new_elseif_list(
2983                             node.getChild(6), endIfNode, attsElse.getControlFlowGraph().getHead());
2984     
2985                         AbstractCfgNode ifNode = new If(
2986                             attsExpr.getPlace(), Constant.TRUE, TacOperators.IS_EQUAL,
2987                             node.getChild(2));
2988     
2989                         connect(attsExpr.getControlFlowGraph(), ifNode);
2990                         connect(ifNode, attsElif.getControlFlowGraph(), CfgEdge.FALSE_EDGE);
2991                         connect(ifNode, attsStatement.getControlFlowGraph(), CfgEdge.TRUE_EDGE);
2992                         connect(attsStatement.getControlFlowGraph(), endIfNode);
2993                         connect(attsElse.getControlFlowGraph(), endIfNode);
2994     
2995                         myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
2996                             attsExpr.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
2997                             endIfNode));
2998                     }
2999     
3000                     break;
3001                 }
3002     
3003                 // -> T_WHILE ( expr ) while_statement
3004                 case PhpSymbols.T_WHILE: {
3005                     AbstractCfgNode endWhileNode = new Empty();
3006                     this.breakTargetStack.add(endWhileNode);
3007                     int logId = this.tempId;
3008                     TacAttributes attsExpr = this.expr(node.getChild(2));
3009                     this.resetId(logId);
3010                     this.continueTargetStack.add(attsExpr.getControlFlowGraph().getHead());
3011                     TacAttributes attsStatement = this.while_statement(node.getChild(4));
3012     
3013                     AbstractCfgNode ifNode = new If(
3014                         attsExpr.getPlace(), Constant.TRUE, TacOperators.IS_EQUAL,
3015                         node.getChild(2));
3016     
3017                     connect(attsExpr.getControlFlowGraph(), ifNode);
3018                     connect(ifNode, attsStatement.getControlFlowGraph(), CfgEdge.TRUE_EDGE);
3019                     connect(ifNode, endWhileNode, CfgEdge.FALSE_EDGE);
3020                     connect(attsStatement.getControlFlowGraph(), attsExpr.getControlFlowGraph());
3021     
3022                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
3023                         attsExpr.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
3024                         endWhileNode));
3025     
3026                     this.continueTargetStack.removeLast();
3027                     this.breakTargetStack.removeLast();
3028     
3029                     break;
3030                 }
3031     
3032                 // -> T_DO statement T_WHILE ( expr ) ;
3033                 case PhpSymbols.T_DO: {
3034                     AbstractCfgNode endDoNode = new Empty();
3035                     this.breakTargetStack.add(endDoNode);
3036                     TacAttributes attsStatement = this.statement(node.getChild(1));
3037                     int logId = this.tempId;
3038                     TacAttributes attsExpr = this.expr(node.getChild(4));
3039                     this.resetId(logId);
3040                     this.continueTargetStack.add(attsStatement.getControlFlowGraph().getHead());
3041     
3042                     AbstractCfgNode ifNode = new If(
3043                         attsExpr.getPlace(), Constant.TRUE, TacOperators.IS_EQUAL,
3044                         node.getChild(4));
3045     
3046                     connect(attsStatement.getControlFlowGraph(), attsExpr.getControlFlowGraph());
3047                     connect(attsExpr.getControlFlowGraph(), ifNode);
3048                     connect(ifNode, attsStatement.getControlFlowGraph(), CfgEdge.TRUE_EDGE);
3049                     connect(ifNode, endDoNode, CfgEdge.FALSE_EDGE);
3050     
3051                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
3052                         attsStatement.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
3053                         endDoNode));
3054     
3055                     this.continueTargetStack.removeLast();
3056                     this.breakTargetStack.removeLast();
3057     
3058                     break;
3059                 }
3060     
3061                 // -> T_FOR ( for_expr1 ; for_expr2 ; for_expr3 ) for_statement
3062                 case PhpSymbols.T_FOR: {
3063                     AbstractCfgNode endForNode = new Empty();
3064                     this.breakTargetStack.add(endForNode);
3065     
3066                     TacAttributes attsExpr1 = this.for_expr(node.getChild(2));
3067                     TacAttributes attsExpr2 = this.for_expr(node.getChild(4));
3068                     TacAttributes attsExpr3 = this.for_expr(node.getChild(6));
3069     
3070                     this.continueTargetStack.add(attsExpr3.getControlFlowGraph().getHead());
3071     
3072                     TacAttributes attsStatement = this.for_statement(node.getChild(8));
3073     
3074                     AbstractCfgNode ifNode = new If(
3075                         attsExpr2.getPlace(), Constant.TRUE, TacOperators.IS_EQUAL,
3076                         node.getChild(4));
3077     
3078                     connect(attsExpr1.getControlFlowGraph(), attsExpr2.getControlFlowGraph());

3571         /**
3572          * An expr_without_variable can contain:
3573          *
3574          * - an assignment: cvar T_ASSIGN expr
3575          * - or a new: T_NEW static_or_variable_string ctor_arguments
3576          * - or a scalar: scalar
3577          *
3578          * This is the function that deals with constructs like $foo->bar = 42;.
3579          *
3580          * @param node
3581          *
3582          * @return
3583          */
3584         TacAttributes expr_without_variable(ParseNode node) {
3585             TacAttributes myAtts = new TacAttributes();
3586     
3587             ParseNode firstChild = node.getChild(0);
3588             switch (firstChild.getSymbol()) {
3589                 // -> T_LIST ( assignment_list ) = expr

3597                     connect(attsExpr.getControlFlowGraph(), attsList.getControlFlowGraph());
3598                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
3599                         attsExpr.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
3600                         attsList.getControlFlowGraph().getTail()));
3601     
3602                     myAtts.setPlace(attsExpr.getPlace());
3603                     break;
3604                 }
3605     
3606                 // -> cvar ...
3607                 case PhpSymbols.cvar: {
3608                     switch (node.getChild(1).getSymbol()) {
3609                         // -> cvar = ...
3610                         case PhpSymbols.T_ASSIGN: {
3611                             if (node.getNumChildren() == 3) {
3612                                 // -> cvar = expr
3613                                 TacAttributes atts0 = this.cvar(firstChild);
3614                                 TacAttributes atts2 = this.expr(node.getChild(2));
3615     
3616                                 AbstractCfgNode cfgNode =
3617                                     new AssignSimple(
3618                                         (Variable) atts0.getPlace(),
3619                                         atts2.getPlace(), node);
3620                                 connect(atts0.getControlFlowGraph(), atts2.getControlFlowGraph());
3621                                 connect(atts2.getControlFlowGraph(), cfgNode);
3622     
3623                                 myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
3624                                     atts0.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
3625                                     cfgNode));
3626     
3627                                 myAtts.setPlace(atts0.getPlace());
3628                             } else {
3629                                 switch (node.getChild(3).getSymbol()) {
3630                                     // -> cvar = & w_cvar
3631                                     case PhpSymbols.w_cvar: {
3632                                         TacAttributes atts0 = this.cvar(firstChild);
3633                                         TacAttributes atts3 = this.w_cvar(node.getChild(3));
3634     
3635                                         AbstractCfgNode cfgNode = new AssignReference(
3636                                             (Variable) atts0.getPlace(),
3637                                             (Variable) atts3.getPlace(), node);
3638                                         connect(atts0.getControlFlowGraph(), atts3.getControlFlowGraph());
3639                                         connect(atts3.getControlFlowGraph(), cfgNode);
3640     
3641                                         myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
3642                                             atts0.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
3643                                             cfgNode,
3644                                             CfgEdge.NORMAL_EDGE));
3645                                         myAtts.setPlace(atts0.getPlace());
3646                                         break;
3647                                     }
3648     
3649                                     // -> cvar = & function_call
3650                                     case PhpSymbols.function_call: {
3651                                         TacAttributes attsCvar = this.cvar(firstChild);
3652                                         TacAttributes attsCall = this.function_call(node.getChild(3));
3653     
3654                                         AbstractCfgNode cfgNode = new AssignReference(
3655                                             (Variable) attsCvar.getPlace(),
3656                                             (Variable) attsCall.getPlace(), node);
3657     
3658                                         connect(attsCvar.getControlFlowGraph(), attsCall.getControlFlowGraph());
3659                                         connect(attsCall.getControlFlowGraph(), cfgNode);
3660     
3661                                         myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
3662                                             attsCvar.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
3663                                             cfgNode));
3664                                         myAtts.setPlace(attsCvar.getPlace());
3665     
3666                                         break;
3667                                     }
3668

4282                     paramList.add(new TacActualParameter(deepList.getPlace(), false));
4283     
4284                     ControlFlowGraph execCallControlFlowGraph = this.functionCallHelper(
4285                         "shell_exec", false, null, paramList,
4286                         tempPlace, true, node, null, null);

4288                     connect(deepList.getControlFlowGraph(), execCallControlFlowGraph.getHead());

4290                         deepList.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),

4296                 }

4299                 case PhpSymbols.T_PRINT: {

4302                     TacAttributes atts1 = this.expr(node.getChild(1));
4303                     AbstractCfgNode cfgNode = new Echo(atts1.getPlace(), node);
4304                     connect(atts1.getControlFlowGraph(), cfgNode);

4308                         atts1.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
4309                         cfgNode));

4312                 }

4315                     Utils.bail("expr_without_variable: default: " + firstChild.getName());
4316                 }
4317             }
4318

4320         }

4520         // - place
4521         TacAttributes function_call(ParseNode node) {
4522             TacAttributes myAtts = new TacAttributes();
4523     
4524             // temporary variable for catching the function's return value
4525             Variable tempVar = newTemp();
4526     
4527             if (node.getChild(0).getSymbol() == PhpSymbols.cvar) {
4528                 // -> cvar ( function_call_parameter_list )
4529     
4530                 // dynamic dispatch problem! examples:
4531                 // $a(...)
4532                 // $a->foo(...)
4533     
4534                 TacAttributes attsList = this.function_call_parameter_list(node.getChild(2));
4535                 TacAttributes attsCvar = this.cvar(node.getChild(0), attsList.getActualParamList(), tempVar);
4536     
4537                 // distinguish between a literal method call and a variable function call
4538                 // (or something else that we could not resolve)
4539                 if (attsCvar.isKnownCall()) {
4540                     // method call
4541                     connect(attsList.getControlFlowGraph(), attsCvar.getControlFlowGraph());
4542     
4543                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
4544                         attsList.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
4545                         attsCvar.getControlFlowGraph().getTail()));
4546     
4547                     myAtts.setPlace(attsCvar.getPlace());
4548                 } else {
4549                     // variable function call
4550     
4551                     // DON'T add it to the global backpatching list:
4552                     // backpatching won't be able to resolve the name
4553                     //callControlFlowGraph = this.functionCallHelper(
4554                     //functionNamePlace.toString(), false, this.unknownFunction, attsList.getActualParamList(),
4555                     //tempPlace, false, node);
4556     
4557                     // simply use a cfgnodecallunknown
4558                     CallUnknownFunction callUnknown = new CallUnknownFunction(
4559                         attsCvar.getPlace().toString(), attsList.getActualParamList(),
4560                         tempVar, node, false);
4561                     ControlFlowGraph callControlFlowGraph = new ControlFlowGraph(callUnknown, callUnknown);
4562     
4563                     connect(attsCvar.getControlFlowGraph(), attsList.getControlFlowGraph());
4564                     connect(attsList.getControlFlowGraph(), callControlFlowGraph.getHead());
4565     
4566                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
4567                         attsCvar.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
4568                         callControlFlowGraph.getTail()));
4569     
4570                     myAtts.setPlace(tempVar);
4571     
4572                     // LATER: if Literals Propagation succeeds in resolving the
4573                     // function's name, it has to adjust the following assignment
4574                     // node responsible for catching the function's return value
4575                 }
4576             } else if (node.getChild(1).getSymbol() == PhpSymbols.T_OPEN_BRACES) {
4577                 // -> T_STRING ( function_call_parameter_list )
4578                 TacAttributes attsList = this.function_call_parameter_list(node.getChild(2));
4579                 String functionName = node.getChild(0).getLexeme().toLowerCase();
4580     
4581                 ControlFlowGraph callControlFlowGraph = this.functionCallHelper(
4582                     functionName, false, null, attsList.getActualParamList(),
4583                     tempVar, true, node, null, null);
4584     
4585                 connect(attsList.getControlFlowGraph(), callControlFlowGraph.getHead());
4586     
4587                 myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
4588                     attsList.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
4589                     callControlFlowGraph.getTail()));
4590     
4591                 myAtts.setPlace(tempVar);
4592             } else {
4593                 // -> T_STRING T_PAAMAYIM_NEKUDOTAYIM static_or_variable_string ( function_call_parameter_list )
4594                 // e.g.:
4595                 // $x = Foo::bar();
4596                 TacAttributes attsList = this.function_call_parameter_list(node.getChild(4));
4597     
4598                 String className = node.getChild(0).getLexeme().toLowerCase();
4599     
4600                 // quick hack: get the method's name
4601                 String methodName = null;
4602                 try {
4603                     ParseNode nameNode = node.getChild(2).getChild(0);
4604                     if (nameNode.getSymbol() == PhpSymbols.T_STRING) {
4605                         methodName = nameNode.getLexeme().toLowerCase() + InternalStrings.methodSuffix;
4606                     }
4607                 } catch (NullPointerException e) {
4608                     // do nothing
4609                 }
4610     
4611                 ControlFlowGraph callControlFlowGraph;
4612                 if (methodName == null) {
4613                     // simply use a cfgnodecallunknown
4614                     CallUnknownFunction callUnknown = new CallUnknownFunction(
4615                         "<unknown>", attsList.getActualParamList(), tempVar, node, true);
4616                     callControlFlowGraph = new ControlFlowGraph(callUnknown, callUnknown);
4617                 } else {
4618                     // try to backpatch
4619                     callControlFlowGraph = this.functionCallHelper(
4620                         methodName, true, null, attsList.getActualParamList(),
4621                         tempVar, true, node, className, null);
4622                 }
4623     
4624                 connect(attsList.getControlFlowGraph(), callControlFlowGraph.getHead());
4625     
4626                 myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
4627                     attsList.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
4628                     callControlFlowGraph.getTail()));
4629     
4630                 myAtts.setPlace(tempVar);
4631             }
4632     
4633             return myAtts;
4634         }

4831                             cfgNode));

4833                         // -> non_empty_array_pair_list , expr T_DOUBLE_ARROW expr
4834                         TacAttributes attsList = this.non_empty_array_pair_list(firstChild, arrayPlace);

4843                         connect(attsExpr2.getControlFlowGraph(), cfgNode);

4845                         myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
4846                             attsList.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
4847                             cfgNode));
4848                     } else {
4849                         // -> non_empty_array_pair_list , expr T_DOUBLE_ARROW & w_cvar
4850                         TacAttributes attsList = this.non_empty_array_pair_list(firstChild, arrayPlace);
4851                         TacAttributes attsExpr1 = this.expr(node.getChild(2));
4852                         TacAttributes attsCvar = this.w_cvar(node.getChild(5));
4853     
4854                         AbstractCfgNode cfgNode = this.arrayPairListHelper(
4855                             arrayPlace, attsExpr1.getPlace(), attsCvar.getPlace(), true, node);
4856     
4857                         connect(attsList.getControlFlowGraph(), attsExpr1.getControlFlowGraph());
4858                         connect(attsExpr1.getControlFlowGraph(), attsCvar.getControlFlowGraph());
4859                         connect(attsCvar.getControlFlowGraph(), cfgNode);
4860     
4861                         myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
4862                             attsList.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
4863                             cfgNode));
4864                     }
4865     
4866                     break;
4867                 }
4868     
4869                 // -> expr ...
4870                 case PhpSymbols.expr: {
4871                     if (node.getNumChildren() == 1) {
4872                         // -> expr
4873                         TacAttributes attsExpr = this.expr(firstChild);
4874     
4875                         AbstractCfgNode cfgNode = this.arrayPairListHelper(
4876                             arrayPlace, new Literal("0"), attsExpr.getPlace(), false, node);
4877     
4878                         connect(attsExpr.getControlFlowGraph(), cfgNode);
4879     
4880                         myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
4881                             attsExpr.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
4882                             cfgNode));
4883     
4884                         myAtts.setArrayIndex(0);
4885                     } else if (node.getChild(2).getSymbol() == PhpSymbols.expr) {
4886                         // -> expr T_DOUBLE_ARROW expr
4887                         TacAttributes attsExpr1 = this.expr(firstChild);
4888                         TacAttributes attsExpr2 = this.expr(node.getChild(2));
4889     
4890                         AbstractCfgNode cfgNode = this.arrayPairListHelper(
4891                             arrayPlace, attsExpr1.getPlace(), attsExpr2.getPlace(), false, node);
4892     
4893                         connect(attsExpr1.getControlFlowGraph(), attsExpr2.getControlFlowGraph());
4894                         connect(attsExpr2.getControlFlowGraph(), cfgNode);
4895     
4896                         myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
4897                             attsExpr1.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
4898                             cfgNode));
4899                     } else {
4900                         // -> expr T_DOUBLE_ARROW & w_cvar
4901                         TacAttributes attsExpr1 = this.expr(firstChild);
4902                         TacAttributes attsCvar = this.w_cvar(node.getChild(3));
4903     
4904                         AbstractCfgNode cfgNode = this.arrayPairListHelper(
4905                             arrayPlace, attsExpr1.getPlace(), attsCvar.getPlace(), true, node);
4906     
4907                         connect(attsExpr1.getControlFlowGraph(), attsCvar.getControlFlowGraph());
4908                         connect(attsCvar.getControlFlowGraph(), cfgNode);
4909     
4910                         myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
4911                             attsExpr1.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
4912                             cfgNode));
4913                     }
4914     
4915                     break;
4916                 }
4917     
4918                 // -> & w_cvar
4919                 case PhpSymbols.T_BITWISE_AND: {
4920                     TacAttributes attsCvar = this.w_cvar(node.getChild(1));
4921     
4922                     AbstractCfgNode cfgNode = this.arrayPairListHelper(
4923                         arrayPlace, new Literal("0"), attsCvar.getPlace(), true, node);
4924     
4925                     connect(attsCvar.getControlFlowGraph(), cfgNode);
4926     
4927                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
4928                         attsCvar.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
4929                         cfgNode));
4930     
4931                     break;
4932                 }
4933             }
4934     
4935             this.resetId(logId);
4936             return myAtts;
4937         }

5119         // - cfg
5120         // - place
5121         TacAttributes variable_name(
5122             ParseNode node, Variable leftPlace, List<TacActualParameter> paramList, Variable catchVar
5123         ) {
5124             TacAttributes myAtts = new TacAttributes();
5125     
5126             ParseNode firstChild = node.getChild(0);
5127             switch (firstChild.getSymbol()) {
5128                 // -> T_STRING
5129                 case PhpSymbols.T_STRING: {
5130                     if (paramList != null) {
5131                         // a method call
5132                         // the method's name
5133                         String methodName = firstChild.getLexeme().toLowerCase() + InternalStrings.methodSuffix;
5134                         // if this call is applied on $this, we can easily extract the classname
5135                         String className = null;
5136                         if (leftPlace.getName().equals("$this")) {
5137                             className = this.classStack.getLast().getName();
5138                         }
5139                         // make a cfg for this method call
5140                         ControlFlowGraph callControlFlowGraph = this.functionCallHelper(
5141                             methodName, true, null, paramList,
5142                             catchVar, true, node, className, leftPlace);
5143                         myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(callControlFlowGraph);
5144                         myAtts.setPlace(catchVar);
5145                         myAtts.setIsKnownCall(true);
5146                     } else {
5147                         // access to a member variable
5148                         AbstractCfgNode emptyNode = new Empty();
5149                         myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(emptyNode, emptyNode));
5150                         myAtts.setPlace(this.memberPlace);
5151                         myAtts.setIsKnownCall(false);
5152                     }
5153                     break;
5154                 }
5155     
5156                 // -> T_OPEN_CURLY_BRACES expr T_CLOSE_CURLY_BRACES
5157                 case PhpSymbols.T_OPEN_CURLY_BRACES: {
5158                     // evaluate the expression (such that possible side-effects
5159                     // are handled)
5160                     TacAttributes atts1 = this.expr(node.getChild(1));
5161                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(atts1.getControlFlowGraph());
5162                     // ...but don't try to find out which member/method is accessed
5163                     myAtts.setPlace(this.memberPlace);
5164                     myAtts.setIsKnownCall(false);
5165                     break;
5166                 }
5167             }
5168     
5169             return myAtts;
5170         }

5354         TacAttributes scalar(ParseNode node) {
5355             TacAttributes myAtts = new TacAttributes();
5356     
5357             ParseNode firstChild = node.getChild(0);
5358             switch (firstChild.getSymbol()) {
5359     
5360                 // -> T_STRING
5361                 // a string without enclosing quotes = a defined constant (or the
5362                 // string, of there is no such constant); true and false (and all
5363                 // case-insensitive variants) also fall into this category;
5364                 // constants must have been defined before their use (unlike functions);
5365                 // magic constants have their own tokens under common_scalar
5366                 case PhpSymbols.T_STRING: {
5367                     AbstractCfgNode cfgNode = new Empty();
5368                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(cfgNode, cfgNode));
5369                     myAtts.setPlace(makeConstantPlace(firstChild.getLexeme()));
5370                     break;
5371                 }
5372     
5373                 // -> T_STRING_VARNAME
5374                 case PhpSymbols.T_STRING_VARNAME: {
5375                     // ex. a in "${a}"
5376                     AbstractCfgNode cfgNode = new Empty();
5377                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(cfgNode, cfgNode));
5378                     myAtts.setPlace(new Literal(firstChild.getLexeme()));
5379                     break;
5380                 }
5381     
5382                 // -> common_scalar
5383                 case PhpSymbols.common_scalar: {
5384                     TacAttributes atts0 = this.common_scalar(firstChild);
5385                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(atts0.getControlFlowGraph());
5386                     myAtts.setPlace(atts0.getPlace());
5387                     break;
5388                 }
5389     
5390                 // -> " encaps_list "
5391                 // double quotes enclosing something that also contains at least
5392                 // one variable
5393                 case PhpSymbols.T_DOUBLE_QUOTE: {
5394                     TacAttributes attsList = this.encaps_list(node.getChild(1));
5395     
5396                     EncapsList encapsList = attsList.getEncapsList();
5397                     TacAttributes deepList = encapsList.makeAtts(newTemp(), node);
5398                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(deepList.getControlFlowGraph());
5399                     myAtts.setPlace(deepList.getPlace());
5400     
5401                     break;
5402                 }
5403     
5404                 // -> ' encaps_list '
5405                 case PhpSymbols.T_SINGLE_QUOTE: {
5406                     // seems to be an unreachable production
5407                     System.out.println(node.getLoc());
5408                     throw new RuntimeException("scalar: unreachable position?");
5409                     //break;
5410                 }
5411     
5412                 // -> T_START_HEREDOC encaps_list T_END_HEREDOC
5413                 // works the same way as " encaps_list "
5414                 case PhpSymbols.T_START_HEREDOC: {
5415                     TacAttributes attsList = this.encaps_list(node.getChild(1));
5416     
5417                     EncapsList encapsList = attsList.getEncapsList();
5418                     TacAttributes deepList = encapsList.makeAtts(newTemp(), node);
5419                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(deepList.getControlFlowGraph());
5420                     myAtts.setPlace(deepList.getPlace());
5421     
5422                     break;
5423                 }
5424             }
5425     
5426             return myAtts;
5427         }

5429         // - NO cfg
5430         // - NO place
5431         // - encapsList
5432         TacAttributes encaps_list(ParseNode node) {
5433             TacAttributes myAtts = new TacAttributes();
5434     
5435             ParseNode firstChild = node.getChild(0);
5436             if (firstChild.getSymbol() == PhpSymbols.T_EPSILON) {
5437                 // -> empty
5438                 myAtts.setEncapsList(new EncapsList());
5439                 return myAtts;
5440             }
5441     
5442             ParseNode secondChild = node.getChild(1);
5443             switch (secondChild.getSymbol()) {
5444                 // -> encaps_list encaps_var
5445                 case PhpSymbols.encaps_var: {
5446                     TacAttributes attsList = this.encaps_list(firstChild);
5447                     TacAttributes attsVar = this.encaps_var(secondChild);
5448     
5449                     EncapsList encapsList = attsList.getEncapsList();
5450                     encapsList.add(attsVar.getPlace(), attsVar.getControlFlowGraph());
5451                     myAtts.setEncapsList(encapsList);
5452                     break;
5453                 }
5454     
5455                 // -> encaps_list T_STRING
5456                 case PhpSymbols.T_STRING: {
5457                     this.encapsListHelper(node, myAtts);
5458                     break;
5459                 }
5460     
5461                 // -> encaps_list T_NUM_STRING
5462                 case PhpSymbols.T_NUM_STRING: {
5463                     this.encapsListHelper(node, myAtts);
5464                     break;
5465                 }
5466     
5467                 // -> encaps_list T_ENCAPSED_AND_WHITESPACE
5468                 case PhpSymbols.T_ENCAPSED_AND_WHITESPACE: {
5469                     this.encapsListHelper(node, myAtts);
5470                     break;
5471                 }
5472     
5473                 // -> encaps_list T_CHARACTER
5474                 // escaped character?
5475                 case PhpSymbols.T_CHARACTER: {
5476                     this.encapsListHelper(node, myAtts);
5477                     break;
5478                 }
5479     
5480                 // -> encaps_list T_BAD_CHARACTER
5481                 case PhpSymbols.T_BAD_CHARACTER: {
5482                     // the token T_BAD_CHARACTER is never returned by the scanner
5483                     Utils.bail("encaps_list: unreachable position?");
5484                     break;
5485                 }
5486     
5487                 // -> encaps_list [
5488                 case PhpSymbols.T_OPEN_RECT_BRACES: {
5489                     this.encapsListHelper(node, myAtts);
5490                     break;
5491                 }
5492     
5493                 // -> encaps_list ]
5494                 case PhpSymbols.T_CLOSE_RECT_BRACES: {
5495                     this.encapsListHelper(node, myAtts);
5496                     break;
5497                 }
5498     
5499                 // -> encaps_list {
5500                 case PhpSymbols.T_OPEN_CURLY_BRACES: {
5501                     this.encapsListHelper(node, myAtts);
5502                     break;
5503                 }
5504     
5505                 // -> encaps_list }
5506                 case PhpSymbols.T_CLOSE_CURLY_BRACES: {
5507                     this.encapsListHelper(node, myAtts);
5508                     break;
5509                 }
5510     
5511                 // -> encaps_list T_OBJECT_OPERATOR
5512                 case PhpSymbols.T_OBJECT_OPERATOR: {
5513                     this.encapsListHelper(node, myAtts);
5514                     break;
5515                 }
5516             }
5517     
5518             return myAtts;
5519         }

5523         TacAttributes encaps_var(ParseNode node) {
5524             TacAttributes myAtts = new TacAttributes();
5525     
5526             if (node.getNumChildren() == 1) {
5527                 // -> T_VARIABLE
5528                 AbstractCfgNode emptyNode = new Empty();

5530                 myAtts.setPlace(makePlace(node.getChild(0).getLexeme()));

5539                     myAtts.setPlace(this.makeArrayElementPlace(

5549                     AbstractCfgNode emptyNode = new Empty();
5550                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(emptyNode, emptyNode));
5551                     myAtts.setPlace(this.memberPlace);

5569                         arrayPlace,

5573                     break;

5581                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(attsCvar.getControlFlowGraph());

5700         TacAttributes elseif_list(ParseNode node, AbstractCfgNode trueSucc, AbstractCfgNode falseSucc) {
5701             TacAttributes myAtts = new TacAttributes();
5702     
5703             ParseNode firstChild = node.getChild(0);
5704             switch (firstChild.getSymbol()) {
5705

5721

5723                         attsExpr.getPlace(), Constant.TRUE, TacOperators.IS_EQUAL, node.getChild(3));
5724     
5725                     connect(attsExpr.getControlFlowGraph(), ifNode);
5726                     connect(ifNode, falseSucc, CfgEdge.FALSE_EDGE);
5727                     connect(ifNode, attsStatement.getControlFlowGraph(), CfgEdge.TRUE_EDGE);
5728                     connect(attsStatement.getControlFlowGraph(), trueSucc);
5729     
5730                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
5731                         attsElif.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
5732                         attsStatement.getControlFlowGraph().getTail(),
5733                         attsStatement.getControlFlowGraph().getTailEdgeType()));
5734     
5735                     break;
5736                 }
5737             }
5738     
5739             return myAtts;
5740         }

5952         // - defaultNode
5953         TacAttributes switch_case_list(
5954             ParseNode node, AbstractTacPlace switchPlace, AbstractCfgNode nextTest, AbstractCfgNode nextStatement
5955         ) {
5956             ParseNode listNode = null;
5957             switch (node.getChild(2).getSymbol()) {
5958                 // -> { case_list }
5959                 case PhpSymbols.T_CLOSE_CURLY_BRACES: {
5960                     listNode = node.getChild(1);
5961                     break;
5962                 }
5963     
5964                 // -> $0 $1 case_list ...
5965                 case PhpSymbols.case_list: {
5966                     if (node.getChild(0).getSymbol() == PhpSymbols.T_OPEN_CURLY_BRACES) {
5967                         // -> { ; case_list }
5968                         listNode = node.getChild(2);
5969                     } else {
5970                         // -> : ; case_list T_ENDSWITCH ;
5971                         listNode = node.getChild(2);
5972                     }
5973                     break;
5974                 }
5975     
5976                 // -> : case_list T_ENDSWITCH ;
5977                 case PhpSymbols.T_ENDSWITCH: {
5978                     listNode = node.getChild(1);
5979                     break;
5980                 }
5981             }
5982     
5983             TacAttributes myAtts = this.case_list(listNode,
5984                 switchPlace, nextTest, nextStatement);
5985     
5986             return myAtts;
5987         }

5989         // - cfg
5990         // - defaultNode
5991         TacAttributes case_list(
5992             ParseNode node, AbstractTacPlace switchPlace, AbstractCfgNode nextTest, AbstractCfgNode nextStatement
5993         ) {
5994             TacAttributes myAtts = new TacAttributes();
5995     
5996             if (node.getChild(0).getSymbol() == PhpSymbols.T_EPSILON) {
5997                 // -> empty
5998                 AbstractCfgNode emptyNode = new Empty();
5999                 connect(emptyNode, nextTest);
6000                 myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(emptyNode, emptyNode));
6001                 myAtts.setDefaultNode(null);
6002             } else if (node.getChild(1).getSymbol() == PhpSymbols.T_CASE) {
6003                 // -> case_list T_CASE expr case_separator inner_statement_list
6004                 TacAttributes attsExpr = this.expr(node.getChild(2));
6005                 TacAttributes attsStatement = this.inner_statement_list(node.getChild(4));
6006                 TacAttributes attsCaseList = this.case_list(node.getChild(0),
6007                     switchPlace, attsExpr.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(), attsStatement.getControlFlowGraph().getHead());
6008     
6009                 Variable tempPlace = this.newTemp();
6010                 AbstractCfgNode compareNode = new AssignBinary(
6011                     tempPlace, switchPlace, attsExpr.getPlace(), TacOperators.IS_EQUAL, node.getChild(2));
6012                 AbstractCfgNode ifNode = new If(
6013                     tempPlace, Constant.TRUE, TacOperators.IS_EQUAL, node.getChild(2));
6014     
6015                 connect(attsExpr.getControlFlowGraph(), compareNode);
6016                 connect(compareNode, ifNode);
6017                 connect(ifNode, attsStatement.getControlFlowGraph(), CfgEdge.TRUE_EDGE);
6018                 connect(ifNode, nextTest, CfgEdge.FALSE_EDGE);
6019                 connect(attsStatement.getControlFlowGraph(), nextStatement);
6020     
6021                 // the tail doesn't matter
6022                 myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
6023                     attsCaseList.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
6024                     attsCaseList.getControlFlowGraph().getHead()));
6025     
6026                 myAtts.setDefaultNode(attsCaseList.getDefaultNode());
6027             } else {
6028                 // -> case_list T_DEFAULT case_separator inner_statement_list
6029                 TacAttributes attsStatement = this.inner_statement_list(node.getChild(3));
6030                 TacAttributes attsCaseList = this.case_list(node.getChild(0),
6031                     switchPlace, nextTest, attsStatement.getControlFlowGraph().getHead());
6032     
6033                 connect(attsStatement.getControlFlowGraph(), nextStatement);
6034     
6035                 // the tail doesn't matter
6036                 myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
6037                     attsCaseList.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
6038                     attsCaseList.getControlFlowGraph().getHead()));
6039     
6040                 myAtts.setDefaultNode(attsStatement.getControlFlowGraph().getHead());
6041             }
6042     
6043             return myAtts;
6044         }

6046         // - cfg
6047         TacAttributes echo_expr_list(ParseNode node) {
6048             TacAttributes myAtts = new TacAttributes();
6049     
6050             ParseNode firstChild = node.getChild(0);
6051             switch (firstChild.getSymbol()) {
6052     
6053                 // -> echo_expr_list , expr
6054                 case PhpSymbols.echo_expr_list: {
6055                     TacAttributes attsList = this.echo_expr_list(firstChild);
6056                     TacAttributes attsExpr = this.expr(node.getChild(2));
6057     
6058                     AbstractCfgNode cfgNode = new Echo(attsExpr.getPlace(), node);
6059     
6060                     connect(attsList.getControlFlowGraph(), attsExpr.getControlFlowGraph());
6061                     connect(attsExpr.getControlFlowGraph(), cfgNode);
6062     
6063                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
6064                         attsList.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
6065                         cfgNode));
6066     
6067                     break;
6068                 }
6069     
6070                 // -> expr
6071                 case PhpSymbols.expr: {
6072                     TacAttributes atts0 = this.expr(firstChild);
6073                     AbstractCfgNode cfgNode = new Echo(atts0.getPlace(), node);
6074                     connect(atts0.getControlFlowGraph(), cfgNode);
6075                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
6076                         atts0.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
6077                         cfgNode));
6078                     break;
6079                 }
6080             }
6081

6083         }

6156         // - cfg
6157         TacAttributes assignment_list(ParseNode node, AbstractTacPlace arrayPlace, int arrayIndex) {
6158             TacAttributes myAtts = new TacAttributes();
6159     
6160             if (node.getNumChildren() == 3) {
6161                 // -> assignment_list , assignment_list_element
6162                 TacAttributes attsList = this.assignment_list(
6163                     node.getChild(0),
6164                     arrayPlace,
6165                     arrayIndex);
6166                 TacAttributes attsElement = this.assignment_list_element(
6167                     node.getChild(2),
6168                     arrayPlace,
6169                     attsList.getArrayIndex());
6170     
6171                 connect(attsList.getControlFlowGraph(), attsElement.getControlFlowGraph());
6172                 myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
6173                     attsList.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
6174                     attsElement.getControlFlowGraph().getTail()));
6175     
6176                 myAtts.setArrayIndex(attsList.getArrayIndex() + 1);
6177             } else {
6178                 // -> assignment_list_element
6179                 TacAttributes attsElement = this.assignment_list_element(
6180                     node.getChild(0),
6181                     arrayPlace,
6182                     arrayIndex);
6183     
6184                 myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(attsElement.getControlFlowGraph());
6185                 myAtts.setArrayIndex(arrayIndex + 1);
6186             }
6187     
6188             return myAtts;
6189         }
6190     
6191         // - cfg
6192         TacAttributes assignment_list_element(ParseNode node, AbstractTacPlace arrayPlace, int arrayIndex) {
6193             TacAttributes myAtts = new TacAttributes();
6194     
6195             ParseNode firstChild = node.getChild(0);
6196             switch (firstChild.getSymbol()) {
6197                 // -> cvar
6198                 case PhpSymbols.cvar: {
6199                     TacAttributes attsCvar = this.cvar(firstChild);
6200     
6201                     AbstractTacPlace arrayElementPlace = this.makeArrayElementPlace(
6202                         arrayPlace, new Literal(String.valueOf(arrayIndex)));
6203     
6204                     AbstractCfgNode cfgNode = new AssignSimple(
6205                         (Variable) attsCvar.getPlace(),
6206                         arrayElementPlace,
6207                         firstChild);
6208     
6209                     connect(attsCvar.getControlFlowGraph(), cfgNode);
6210     
6211                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(
6212                         attsCvar.getControlFlowGraph().getHead(),
6213                         cfgNode));
6214     
6215                     break;
6216                 }
6217     
6218                 // -> T_LIST ( assignment_list )
6219                 case PhpSymbols.T_LIST: {
6220                     AbstractTacPlace arrayElementPlace = this.makeArrayElementPlace(
6221                         arrayPlace, new Literal(String.valueOf(arrayIndex)));
6222     
6223                     // recurse
6224                     TacAttributes attsList = this.assignment_list(
6225                         node.getChild(2),
6226                         arrayElementPlace,
6227                         0);
6228     
6229                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(attsList.getControlFlowGraph());
6230     
6231                     break;
6232                 }
6233     
6234                 // -> empty
6235                 case PhpSymbols.T_EPSILON: {
6236                     AbstractCfgNode emptyNode = new Empty();
6237                     myAtts.setControlFlowGraph(new ControlFlowGraph(emptyNode, emptyNode));
6238                     break;
6239                 }
6240             }
6241     
6242             return myAtts;
6243         }
